(-3, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Discuss breastfeeding support, postpartum contraception options, and who will help at home in the first two weeks.', 4),
(-3, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Finalising every last small newborn item — easier to judge once baby''s actual size and preferences are known.', 0),
(-3, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Overpacking the hospital bag — many hospitals provide basic supplies; ask what''s included before over-preparing.', 1),
(-3, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Committing to a strict feeding plan before baby arrives — flexibility matters more than a fixed plan at this stage.', 2),
(-3, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'If cleared by your doctor: continue gentle movement, but expect to slow down naturally as balance and energy shift.', 0),
(-3, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest with your feet elevated when possible; swelling is more common now.', 1),
(-3, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Stop exercising and contact your doctor for bleeding, fluid leakage, chest pain, faintness/dizziness, painful regular contractions, or calf pain/swelling.', 2),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Antenatal visits often become more frequent (commonly every two weeks) from this point — confirm your doctor''s schedule.', 0),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Ask your doctor about tetanus/Td vaccination timing if it hasn''t already been completed.', 1),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'At each visit, ask whether blood pressure, weight, urine testing, haemoglobin/anaemia follow-up, fundal-height measurement, and baby''s growth, heart rate, and position/presentation are being assessed as appropriate.', 2),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep your MCP card/records, insurance details, blood group, and emergency contacts together and easily accessible.', 3),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If using public services, ask your ASHA/ANM about PMSMA, JSSK, referral transport, and local maternity entitlements.', 4),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Contact your doctor promptly for a worrying change, reduction, or stopping of movements; vaginal bleeding; fluid leakage; persistent headache; vision changes; sudden facial/hand swelling; severe abdominal pain; or fever.', 5),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'With a bigger bump now, prickly heat and skin chafing (under the belly, between thighs) become more common — keep skin dry, wear breathable fabric.', 6),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Swelling tends to peak with summer heat combined with a heavier bump — rest with feet elevated more often than earlier months.', 7),
(-3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Carry water wherever you go; dehydration risk rises as you''re carrying more weight in the heat.', 8),
(-2, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby continues gaining weight rapidly; fat layers are developing now to help with temperature regulation after birth.', 0),
(-2, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may be head-down by this stage, but many babies still turn until around 36–37 weeks. Your doctor will check and let you know.', 1),
(-2, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Movements may feel different — more stretches and rolls than sharp kicks — but you should continue to feel baby move regularly. Contact your maternity team for any worrying change, reduction, or stopping of movements.', 2),
(-2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Increasing pelvic pressure is common as baby moves lower; Braxton Hicks may become more frequent.', 0),
(-2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Sleep can become harder — extra pillows for support under the belly or between the knees often help.', 1),
(-2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some swelling is normal, but sudden or significant swelling in the face or hands needs prompt attention, not a wait-and-see approach.', 2),
(-2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'A burst of "nesting" energy is common now — fine to act on it in moderation, but rest still matters more than a spotless house.', 3),
(-2, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Finalize who''s helping in the first weeks after baby arrives — don''t leave this vague any longer.', 0),
(-2, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If your hospital bag isn''t fully packed, this is the month to finish it and keep it near the door.', 1),
(-2, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Install the car seat in the actual vehicle you''ll bring baby home in, and test that it''s secure.', 2),
(-2, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any new big purchase decisions — this is the month to lock in what you already have, not start new research.', 0),
(-2, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Unnecessary long-distance travel late in pregnancy, or any travel your doctor has not cleared.', 1),
(-2, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Making plans that assume a specific delivery date — babies rarely stick to the calendar.', 2),
(-2, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue gentle movement if your doctor has cleared it, but expect to slow down further — this is normal, not a setback.', 0),
(-2, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'This is a good month to practice breathing or relaxation techniques you may want to use during labor.', 1),
(-2, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest whenever your body asks — fatigue now is appropriate, not something to push through.', 2),
(-2, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Stop exercising and contact your doctor for bleeding, fluid leakage, chest pain, faintness/dizziness, painful regular contractions, or calf pain/swelling.', 3),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Antenatal visits usually become more frequent now. Many uncomplicated pregnancies are still seen every two weeks until closer to 36 weeks; confirm your doctor''s schedule.', 0),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Ask whether GBS screening is offered or recommended in your hospital; where used, it is generally done at 35–37 weeks.', 1),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Ask your doctor to explain when to contact the hospital: regular worsening contractions, fluid leakage, vaginal bleeding, reduced movements, severe headache/vision changes, fever, or any labour signs before 37 weeks.', 2),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep your MCP card/records, blood group, insurance details, and emergency contacts accessible at all times now — not just "somewhere in the house."', 3),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If using public services, confirm your ASHA/ANM contact and nearest facility/referral transport plan now that delivery is approaching.', 4),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Identify a potential blood donor, primary and backup transport, and the referral hospital as part of your emergency plan.', 5),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Contact your doctor promptly for a worrying change, reduction, or stopping of movements; vaginal bleeding; fluid leakage; persistent headache; vision changes; sudden swelling; severe abdominal pain; fever; or any signs of labour before 37 weeks.', 6),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'With delivery approaching, map out a backup route and backup transport option for reaching the hospital in heavy rain — don''t wait until you''re in labor to think about this.', 7),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Warm, humid weather can make comfort and hygiene harder. Seek advice promptly for burning while urinating, fever, unusual discharge, or feeling unwell.', 8),
(-2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Mosquito-borne illnesses such as dengue and chikungunya need extra caution this close to delivery. Use pregnancy-appropriate repellent, nets/screens, covered clothing, and remove standing water around the home.', 9),
(-1, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'From 37 weeks, baby is early term; development continues, especially in the lungs and brain. Full term begins at 39 weeks.', 0),
(-1, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Weight gain continues but slows slightly as space runs out.', 1),
(-1, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Movements should still be felt regularly, even if they feel more like rolls and presses than sharp kicks. Contact your maternity team for any worrying change, reduction, or stopping of movements.', 2),
(-1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Increased pelvic pressure, more frequent Braxton Hicks, and mild cramping are common as your body prepares for labor.', 0),
(-1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'You may notice the "bloody show" or other early signs — ask your doctor what''s normal to expect and when to actually call.', 1),
(-1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest whenever you can; disrupted sleep now is expected, not a failure on your part.', 2),
(-1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue supplements as prescribed; don''t stop anything without checking with your doctor first.', 3),
(-1, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Confirm your go-bag is fully packed and by the door — this is not a "soon" task anymore.', 0),
