(-1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Use pregnancy-appropriate mosquito repellent, nets/screens, covered clothing, and remove standing water around the home. Seek medical advice promptly for fever.', 9),
(-1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Keep a small set of newborn clothes and linens dry, clean, and ready to use; avoid storing them in a damp cupboard.', 10),
(0, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'In the first days, baby will lose a small amount of weight — this is normal; most babies regain their birth weight by around 10–14 days. Ask the paediatrician if feeding or weight gain is not going as expected.', 0),
(0, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby often sleeps for much of the day and night, waking mainly to feed. Sleep is usually spread across many short stretches, so long alert periods or a predictable routine are not expected yet.', 1),
(0, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Mild jaundice (yellowing of skin/eyes) is common in the first week, but seek prompt medical advice if it starts in the first 24 hours, deepens or spreads, or baby is very sleepy or feeding poorly. Do not use sunlight as treatment.', 2),
(0, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Breastfed babies often feed 8–12 times in 24 hours. If feeding is painful, latching is difficult, or you are worried baby is not getting enough, ask for early feeding support.', 3),
(0, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Vaginal bleeding (lochia) is normal for several weeks, gradually lightening — but soaking a pad within an hour, large clots, or a sudden increase warrants a call to your doctor.', 0),
(0, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you had a C-section, keep the incision clean and dry, and watch for increasing redness, swelling, or discharge.', 1),
(0, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Emotional swings — tearfulness, overwhelm, sudden joy — are common in the first two weeks. If low mood, anxiety, or feeling unlike yourself continues, feels severe, or makes daily life hard, tell your doctor promptly — support is available, and this is not a failure.', 2),
(0, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Thoughts of harming yourself or baby need immediate help. Confusion, hearing or seeing things others do not, extreme agitation, or not sleeping at all can be urgent postpartum mental-health symptoms.', 3),
(0, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Eat when you can, accept help when it''s offered, and don''t measure yourself against how "put together" anyone else looks right now.', 4),
(0, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Newborn-size diapers and a few going-home outfits, if not already sorted.', 0),
(0, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A simple way to track feeds and wet/dirty diapers for the first couple of weeks — a notebook or phone note works fine.', 1),
(0, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Confirm baby''s first paediatrician visit, usually within the first few days of coming home, and ask when the next newborn follow-up should be.', 2),
(0, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep the hospital discharge papers and immunisation card together; check the birth-registration process and the deadline to add baby to health insurance, if applicable.', 3),
(0, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any big decisions about routines, schedules, or "sleep training" — far too early, and babies this age don''t follow predictable patterns yet.', 0),
(0, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Introducing anything besides breast milk or correctly prepared formula — including water, honey, ghutti, herbal remedies, animal milk, or teas — unless your paediatrician has specifically advised it.', 1),
(0, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Comparing your baby, your recovery, or your feeding journey to anyone else''s.', 2),
(0, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For baby: brief, supervised tummy time for a minute or two at a time, several times a day, while awake and watched — on your chest or a firm floor surface, never for sleep.', 0),
(0, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: rest whenever baby rests, if you can — this isn''t laziness, it''s necessary recovery.', 1),
(0, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: gentle walking is usually fine as comfortable after an uncomplicated birth. After a C-section, difficult delivery, complications, or pelvic-floor symptoms, follow your doctor''s individual advice before increasing activity.', 2),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Attend baby''s first paediatric check, usually within the first week, to check weight, jaundice, and feeding. Ask whether another newborn check is needed between days 7 and 14.', 0),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Check the discharge summary and immunisation card for birth-dose vaccinations: BCG, Hepatitis B birth dose, and OPV-0. If any were missed, ask the clinic when they should be given.', 1),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Always place baby on their back to sleep, on a firm flat surface, with nothing else in the sleep space — no pillows, loose blankets, bumpers, or toys. Room-share if possible, but do not bed-share.', 2),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep the umbilical cord stump clean and dry, and apply nothing to it. Seek medical advice for redness spreading onto the skin, pus, a foul smell, or fever.', 3),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent paediatric care for fever, poor feeding, unusual lethargy, difficulty breathing, persistent vomiting, seizures, jaundice that is spreading or worsening, or noticeably fewer wet diapers than expected.', 4),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'For yourself: seek urgent medical advice for heavy bleeding, fever, severe pain, severe headache or vision changes, chest pain or breathlessness, one-sided leg pain/swelling, wound concerns, or thoughts of harming yourself or the baby.', 5),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Dress baby in layers rather than one thick layer, and check warmth by feeling the back of the neck or chest — not hands or feet, which are naturally cooler.', 6),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Overheating from too many blankets or heaters is a real risk, not just a comfort issue — more layers aren''t automatically safer. Keep heaters away from the sleep space, and never use loose covers for sleep.', 7),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Keep skin moisturized as winter air dries it out; avoid strongly fragranced products on newborn skin.', 8),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Protect from sudden temperature changes during outings, but avoid excessive bundling indoors.', 9),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Dress baby in light, breathable cotton; avoid over-bundling even in air-conditioned rooms.', 10),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Watch for heat rash in skin folds (neck, underarms, diaper area) — keep these areas dry and cool.', 11),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Do not give water to a newborn, even in heat, unless your pediatrician specifically advises it — breast milk or formula alone covers hydration needs before 6 months, and extra water can genuinely be harmful this young.', 12),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Keep baby out of direct sunlight; use shade and light clothing during outings rather than sunscreen unless your paediatrician advises otherwise.', 13),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Keep skin dry, especially in folds — humidity worsens fungal and heat rash.', 14),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Limit baby''s exposure to visitors who are unwell; ask all visitors to wash their hands and avoid kissing baby, especially during cold-and-flu season.', 15),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Use mosquito nets/screens, dress baby in light covering clothing, and reduce standing water around the home. Ask your paediatrician before using any repellent on a young newborn.', 16),
(0, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Ensure good ventilation at home even with windows shut against rain, and keep the cord area clean and dry — humidity may slow healing.', 17),
(1, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Social smiles often begin during this period — a genuine response to people, not just a reflex. Every baby develops at their own pace; share any concern at the vaccination visit.', 0),
(1, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may look at faces, watch you move, briefly focus on simple objects, react to loud sounds, and start making small sounds other than crying.', 1),
(1, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Feeding may suddenly become more frequent in this period. This can be normal, but seek feeding support if baby has fewer wet diapers, is not gaining weight as expected, or feeding is painful.', 2),
(1, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'The 6-week visit is an important immunisation visit. Under India''s routine schedule, vaccines commonly due include OPV-1, Pentavalent-1, fIPV-1, Rotavirus-1, and PCV-1; carry and update baby''s immunisation card.', 3),
(1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Your own postpartum check is usually due around now — a good time to discuss physical recovery, mood, feeding, contraception, birth spacing, and returning to activity.', 0),
(1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Ongoing fatigue is common; sleep deprivation accumulates, and resting over housework is a reasonable choice, not a failure.', 1),
(1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If breastfeeding, engorgement or blocked ducts can happen. Seek prompt medical advice for fever, chills, flu-like symptoms, or a hot, red, painful, swollen area of the breast, which can indicate mastitis.', 2),
(1, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If low mood, anxiety, or unwanted intrusive thoughts persist or worsen, raise them at (or before) your check — do not wait if it feels urgent. Any urge, plan, or fear of acting on thoughts of harm needs immediate help.', 3),
(1, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If returning to work is on the horizon, start researching childcare and a feeding plan now — including hand-expression or pumping, safe storage, and who will feed baby.', 0),
(1, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A few age-appropriate toys — high-contrast images or soft rattles — are enough. Choose items without small parts, button batteries, magnets, or loose pieces, and keep toys out of the sleep space.', 1),
(1, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Confirm baby''s health insurance addition and birth registration are complete, if not already done.', 2),
(1, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Starting solids — still months away, regardless of how interested baby seems in your food. Until around 6 months, breast milk or correctly prepared formula is all baby needs; no water is needed.', 0),
(1, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby walkers, jumpers, and long periods in a bouncer or seat — not needed for development, and can carry safety risks.', 1),
(1, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Screens and every gadget marketed as "essential" for this age — faces, voices, floor play, and simple objects matter more than equipment right now.', 2),
(1, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue supervised tummy time while baby is awake, gradually building toward about 30 minutes spread across the day as baby tolerates it.', 0),
(1, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Talk, sing, and make eye contact during everyday care — this is real stimulation, not extra work.', 1),
(1, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: build activity gradually as comfortable after an uncomplicated birth. After a C-section, difficult delivery, complications, or pelvic-floor symptoms, follow your doctor''s individual advice before increasing exercise.', 2),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Attend your own 6-week postpartum check.', 0),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Attend baby''s 6-week vaccination visit. Before leaving, ask what mild side effects to expect, how to take baby''s temperature, and exactly when to call. Do not give medicine unless the clinic has advised the correct product and dose.', 1),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep practices exactly as last month: back sleeping, firm flat surface, nothing else in the sleep space, room-sharing without bed-sharing.', 2),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent paediatric advice for a temperature of 38°C or above in a baby under 3 months, poor feeding, unusual lethargy, difficulty breathing, persistent vomiting, seizures, or anything that genuinely worries you — even after vaccination.', 3),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'For yourself: the serious warning signs from Month 1 still apply, including heavy bleeding, fever, severe pain, chest pain/breathlessness, severe headache or vision changes, one-sided leg pain/swelling, wound concerns, or worsening mood and anxiety.', 4),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Continue layering and checking warmth at the neck or chest, not hands or feet.', 5),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'A mild post-vaccination fever or fussiness can occur. Follow the clinic''s advice, dress baby normally, and do not over-bundle in an attempt to "sweat it out."', 6),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Keep the home smoke-free; closed winter windows can worsen indoor air quality.', 7),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Continue moisturizing dry skin as needed.', 8),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Do not give water; keep baby out of direct sunlight. Breathable cotton and shade during outings are usually enough.', 9),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'As baby becomes a little more alert, outings may increase — avoid peak heat hours and keep baby shaded, not just lightly dressed.', 10),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'After vaccination in summer, keep baby comfortably cool. If baby has a temperature of 38°C or above, seems unwell, feeds poorly, or is unusually sleepy, contact the paediatrician urgently.', 11),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue humidity/rash precautions in skin folds.', 12),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Plan clinic visits around the weather; keep baby dry on the way to appointments, but do not over-bundle.', 13),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Use mosquito nets/screens, reduce standing water around the home, and ask the paediatrician before using repellent on a young baby.', 14),
(1, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Do not assume a fever is only vaccine-related: use the clinic''s guidance and seek urgent advice for a temperature of 38°C or above, or if baby seems unwell.', 15),
(2, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Cooing and gurgling often become more elaborate — baby may start experimenting with different sounds and pitches.', 0),
(2, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Head control is strengthening. Continue supporting baby''s head and offering supervised tummy time; baby may also bring hands to mouth or swipe at a toy during play.', 1),
(2, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Eyes may track moving objects more smoothly. Offer a toy held or placed nearby during supervised floor play — never leave toys hanging over the sleep space.', 2),
(2, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Every baby develops at their own pace — for babies born prematurely, use your paediatrician''s corrected-age guidance rather than calendar age.', 3),
(2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Physical recovery is often further along now, though fatigue can still be real, especially with disrupted sleep continuing.', 0),
(2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Postpartum mood changes can also newly appear later, not only in the first weeks — persistent low mood, anxiety, or feeling unlike yourself at any point in the first year is worth raising with your doctor.', 1),
(2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you discussed contraception or birth spacing at your 6-week check, this is a reasonable time to follow up if you have not already. Pregnancy can happen before periods return.', 2),
(2, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same urgent warning signs as earlier months — heavy bleeding, fever, severe pain, chest pain/breathlessness, severe headache or vision changes, one-sided leg pain/swelling, or any urge, plan, or fear of acting on thoughts of harm.', 3),
(2, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you''re planning to return to work, childcare spots often need booking ahead — this is a good window to start finalising, not just researching.', 0),
(2, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Basic babyproofing can start now as baby''s reach and grasp increase — secure loose cords and furniture, keep small objects and choking hazards out of reach, and never leave baby unattended on a bed, sofa, or changing surface.', 1),
(2, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple developmental toys remain enough — nothing elaborate is needed yet. Choose items without small parts, button batteries, magnets, or loose pieces.', 2),
(2, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Starting solids — still not due until around 6 months; breast milk or correctly prepared formula remains all baby needs.', 0),
(2, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Screens of any kind — not recommended for babies this age.', 1),
(2, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby walkers, jumpers, or long stretches restrained in seats — still not needed for development and can carry safety risks. Do not let baby sleep in a car seat, bouncer, swing, or lounger outside travel; move baby to a firm, flat sleep surface.', 2),
(2, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue tummy time while baby is awake and supervised, working toward around 30 minutes total across the day in whatever short stretches baby tolerates.', 0),
(2, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Talking, reading, and singing continue to matter more than any toy or gadget.', 1),
(2, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue building activity gradually if recovery has been uncomplicated; follow individual advice if you had a C-section, complications, or ongoing pelvic-floor symptoms.', 2),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'The 10-week visit commonly includes OPV-2, Pentavalent-2, and Rotavirus-2 under India''s National Immunization Schedule — carry and update baby''s immunisation card. PCV-2 is usually due at 14 weeks; follow your clinic''s schedule.', 0),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Ask the clinic what mild side effects to expect, how to take baby''s temperature, and exactly when to call. Do not give medicine unless the clinic has advised the correct product and dose.', 1),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep practices unchanged: back sleeping, firm flat surface, nothing else in the sleep space, room-sharing without bed-sharing.', 2),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As baby starts reaching and grasping, check the floor and sleep space for small objects, button batteries, magnets, and loose items within reach.', 3),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'At this age, seek same-day paediatric advice for any fever or signs that baby is unwell. For a baby under 3 months, a temperature of 38°C or above is urgent; also seek help for poor feeding, unusual lethargy, difficulty breathing, persistent vomiting, seizures, or anything that genuinely worries you.', 4),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Keep baby out of direct sunlight; breathable cotton and shade remain the rule during outings.', 5),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Watch for heat rash in skin folds, and keep these areas dry and cool.', 6),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'No water for baby, even in heat — breast milk or formula alone still covers hydration needs before 6 months.', 7),
(2, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'For you: keep water nearby and drink regularly or to thirst, especially if breastfeeding; rest in the heat when you can.', 8),
(3, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Head control is often steadier now, and baby may push up onto forearms more confidently during tummy time.', 0),
(3, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Chuckling or laughing out loud may begin, alongside more varied babbling sounds and back-and-forth "conversations" with you.', 1),
(3, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may start reaching for and grasping objects more deliberately, and bringing hands together at midline.', 2),
(3, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 3),
(3, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Many mums feel a sense of settling into rhythm by now, though every family''s pace is different — comparison isn''t useful here.', 0),
(3, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you are breastfeeding and considering returning to work soon, this is a good window to practise hand expression or pumping and learn safe storage and transport. A large stored-milk supply is not essential.', 1),
(3, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same warning signs as previous months — mood changes can still newly emerge at any point in the first year.', 2),
(3, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If periods have returned, or if you''re managing contraception, this is worth revisiting with your doctor if anything''s changed.', 3),
(3, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If daycare or a caregiver arrangement is starting soon, finalize logistics now rather than the week before.', 0),
(3, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A play mat or gym with secure, age-appropriate toys suits this stage well — use it only for awake, supervised floor play, never over or inside the sleep space.', 1),
(3, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you have not already, this is a good time to discuss readiness signs and a plan for introducing solids around 6 months, so you are not scrambling later.', 2),
(3, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Solids — still not due until around 6 months; no need to start early even if baby watches you eat with interest.', 0),
(3, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'There is no need to begin a structured sleep-training programme this month. Continue responsive feeds and comforting; discuss sleep concerns with your paediatrician rather than following generic advice online.', 1),
(3, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Overloading on toys — a few well-chosen ones matter more than many.', 2),
(3, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue tummy time while baby is awake and supervised, working toward around 30 minutes total across the day in whatever short stretches baby tolerates.', 0),
(3, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Encourage reaching and grasping during play — simple, safe objects are enough.', 1),
(3, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: if you have not resumed normal activity yet, build back gradually as comfortable. After a C-section, complications, or pelvic-floor symptoms, follow your doctor''s individual advice.', 2),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'The 14-week visit commonly includes OPV-3, Pentavalent-3, Rotavirus-3, fIPV-2, and PCV-2 under India''s National Immunization Schedule — carry and update baby''s immunisation card, and follow your clinic''s schedule.', 0),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Ask the clinic what mild side effects to expect, how to take baby''s temperature, and exactly when to call. Do not give medicine unless the clinic has advised the correct product and dose.', 1),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep unchanged: back sleeping, firm flat surface, nothing else in the sleep space, room-sharing without bed-sharing.', 2),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As baby becomes more active with reaching — and rolling may begin soon — recheck your space for small objects, cords, button batteries, magnets, and anything newly within reach. Never leave baby unattended on an elevated surface.', 3),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'At this age, seek same-day paediatric advice for any fever or signs that baby is unwell. If baby is under 3 months, a temperature of 38°C or above is urgent; also seek help for poor feeding, unusual lethargy, difficulty breathing, persistent vomiting, seizures, or anything that genuinely worries you.', 4),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Keep baby out of direct sunlight and do not give water — breast milk or correctly prepared formula still provides hydration before 6 months.', 5),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Watch for heat rash in skin folds, especially as baby becomes more mobile and sweatier during play.', 6),
(3, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'For you: keep water nearby and drink regularly or to thirst, especially if breastfeeding; rest in the heat when you can.', 7),
(4, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rolling — tummy to back, and sometimes back to tummy — may be becoming more established. Always give baby safe, supervised floor time to practise.', 0),
(4, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Many babies sit with support now and may lean on their hands while sitting; steady independent sitting usually comes later. Every baby develops at their own pace.', 1),
(4, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Mouthing objects, laughing, squealing, and taking turns making sounds with you are all common at this stage. Drooling on its own is not a sign of readiness for solids.', 2),
(4, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 3),
(4, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Feeding routines may feel more settled by now, though every baby''s pattern is different.', 0),
(4, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same warning signs as previous months — mood changes can still newly emerge at any point in the first year.', 1),
(4, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you''re pumping or expressing as part of a work routine, this is often when it starts feeling more manageable — if it still feels hard, that''s worth mentioning to a lactation consultant or your doctor, not just pushing through.', 2),
(4, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest remains as valid a priority now as it was in month one, even if it looks different.', 3),
(4, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Start researching (not necessarily buying yet) an upright, stable high chair with a secure harness and easy-to-clean surface, plus only basic feeding equipment, ahead of solids around 6 months.', 0),
(4, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue babyproofing as mobility increases — rolling and reaching mean baby can suddenly reach a wider area. Move small objects, cords, button batteries, and magnets out of reach.', 1),
(4, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If helpful, note your baby''s approximate 9-month visit on the calendar. Under India''s government schedule, this is usually the next routine vaccine visit; private or clinic schedules may differ, so follow baby''s immunisation card.', 2),
(4, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Solids — still not due until around 6 months. Drooling, watching you eat, or mouthing hands are common at this age and aren''t, on their own, signs of readiness.', 0),
(4, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Avoid baby walkers — they are unsafe even with an adult nearby. Jumpers and screens are not needed; real floor play and interaction are better for this stage.', 1),
(4, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Forcing sitting or rolling practice — babies get there at their own pace; your role is a safe space to practice, not a schedule to hit.', 2),
(4, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'More floor time matters now — create a safe, supervised space to roll, reach, and gradually work toward sitting. Put a favourite safe toy just out of reach to encourage movement.', 0),
(4, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Follow baby''s own interest in sitting rather than propping for long stretches. During every sleep, place baby on their back; if baby is swaddled, stop swaddling as soon as they show any attempt to roll.', 1),
(4, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue building activity as feels right; if you haven''t already resumed normal exercise, there''s no deadline to do so.', 2),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'There is typically no routine government vaccination visit due this month under India''s National Immunization Schedule; the next routine visit is usually around 9 completed months. Private or clinic schedules may include additional vaccines, so follow baby''s immunisation card and contact your paediatrician with questions.', 0),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep practices unchanged: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space. If baby rolls independently, do not use pillows, wedges, or positioners to hold them in place.', 1),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As rolling becomes more reliable, never leave baby unattended on a bed, changing table, sofa, or any elevated surface, even briefly.', 2),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'For a baby aged 3–6 months, seek same-day paediatric advice for a temperature of 39°C or higher, or sooner if baby seems unwell. Use your paediatrician''s advice for your baby''s individual situation.', 3),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek help promptly for poor feeding, unusual sleepiness, breathing difficulty, persistent vomiting, seizures, a rash that does not fade when pressed, or anything that genuinely worries you.', 4),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Increased floor time means more contact with the floor — keep it clean and dry, especially during humid weeks. Wash and dry toys that are regularly mouthed.', 5),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Use light clothing that covers arms and legs outdoors, and mosquito netting over prams or carriers. If you use repellent, follow the label and ask your paediatrician if unsure.', 6),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Drool combined with humidity can worsen chin/neck rash — pat dry gently and often rather than wiping hard. Use a clean, dry bib and change it when damp.', 7),
(4, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Keep an eye on common monsoon illnesses circulating around you; reasonable caution with sick visitors still applies. Before 6 months, do not give water — breast milk or correctly prepared formula provides hydration.', 8),
(5, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Sitting with less support may become more common, working toward independent sitting. Baby may roll tummy-to-back and may begin rolling both ways; every baby develops at their own pace.', 0),
(5, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Real readiness signs for solids may appear around now: steady head and neck control, sitting with support, opening the mouth for food, and swallowing rather than consistently pushing food back out.', 1),
(5, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Laughing, squealing, taking turns making sounds with you, and putting objects in the mouth to explore are all common at this stage.', 2),
(5, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely — solids readiness follows corrected age too, not just calendar age.', 3),
(5, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Starting solids is a real adjustment — messy, slow, and not about quantity yet. Breast milk or formula remains baby''s main source of nutrition for now; begin with small tastes and build gradually.', 0),
(5, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months.', 1),
(5, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'New routines (solid feeding, a more mobile baby) add real mental load — it''s fine to feel like you''re adjusting all over again.', 2),
(5, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid now as month one.', 3),
(5, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you researched a high chair last month, this is the month to get it set up. Choose a stable, upright chair with a secure harness and an easy-to-clean surface.', 0),
(5, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'First-food basics: thick, soft, mashed home foods such as dal-khichdi, mashed dal, well-cooked vegetables, fruit, egg, or soft lentil/cereal preparations. Include iron-rich options from the start.', 1),
(5, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A washable mat or bib setup and a small open cup for supervised sips of water with meals — this stage is genuinely messy, and that is normal.', 2),
(5, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Honey — not safe before age 1, due to infant botulism risk.', 0),
(5, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Added salt, added sugar, juice, tea, sugary drinks, and packaged baby snacks or biscuits.', 1),
(5, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole grapes, nuts, popcorn, chunks of meat or cheese, raw apple/carrot, or thick spoonfuls of peanut butter — modify texture appropriately instead.', 2),
(5, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Cow''s milk as a main drink — wait until 12 months. Breast milk or correctly prepared infant formula remains baby''s main milk drink before then.', 3),
(5, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe, supervised floor time and sitting practice. Offer food only when baby is seated upright in the high chair — never in a car seat, stroller, recliner, or while crawling or playing.', 0),
(5, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some families offer soft finger foods baby feeds themselves, while others start with spoon-fed mashed foods — both are valid when textures are safe. After a few first foods are tolerated, introduce well-cooked egg and smooth, thinned peanut paste in tiny amounts; ask your paediatrician first if baby has severe eczema or a known food allergy.', 1),
(5, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: rest remains a priority, even as the day gets busier with a new feeding routine.', 2),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'There is typically no routine government vaccination visit due at 6 months under India''s National Immunization Schedule. A paediatric review can still be a good time to discuss starting solids, growth, and your clinic''s private-vaccine schedule.', 0),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Iron-rich first foods matter now. Ask your paediatrician whether baby needs vitamin D or iron supplementation based on feeding, growth, and medical history.', 1),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'New choking-hazard awareness is essential as solids begin — stay within arm''s reach during every feed, and encourage all regular caregivers to learn infant choking first aid.', 2),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep practices unchanged: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space.', 3),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If baby is 3–6 months old, a temperature of 39°C or higher needs same-day paediatric advice. Once baby is over 6 months, seek advice for a fever of 39°C or higher or whenever baby seems unwell; get help promptly for poor feeding, unusual sleepiness, breathing difficulty, persistent vomiting, seizures, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 4),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Food hygiene matters more now with new solids in humid weather — prepare food fresh where possible, cook thoroughly, use clean prep surfaces, and refrigerate promptly or discard leftovers rather than leaving food out.', 5),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Wash your own hands and baby''s hands before every feed, not just after. Use clean utensils and avoid feeding from bottles or teats.', 6),
(5, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue mosquito protection and reasonable caution with unwell visitors. Keep baby''s feeding area and washable bibs dry to help prevent damp-skin rashes.', 7),
(6, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may sit with less support or sit independently for short periods; steadiness varies widely and develops at different times. There is no need to rush sitting practice.', 0),
(6, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Babbling may become more varied, including repeated syllables such as "bababa" or "dadada." Responding warmly helps build the back-and-forth of communication.', 1),
(6, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies begin experimenting with early crawling movements — rocking on hands and knees, scooting, rolling, or commando-crawling. Others take longer, and that is normal too.', 2),
(6, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 3),
(6, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Solids are likely a few weeks in now — appetite and interest can vary a lot day to day, and that''s normal, not a feeding failure.', 0),
(6, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months.', 1),
(6, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you''re managing pumping, solids, and a more mobile baby together, feeling stretched thin is a reasonable response to a genuinely fuller plate, not a sign you''re doing it wrong.', 2),
(6, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest remains a priority, even if it looks like five quiet minutes instead of a nap.', 3),
(6, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Do a final babyproofing pass as mobility increases: anchor heavy furniture and TVs; secure low cabinets with medicines, cleaners, sharp items, and small objects; and keep cords, button batteries, magnets, and pet food out of reach. Use stair gates where needed.', 0),
(6, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 2–3 small meals a day alongside regular breast milk or formula feeds. Gradually make food thicker and more varied; soft finger foods are fine when baby can sit well and bring food to their mouth. Continue iron-rich foods daily.', 1),
(6, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Consider a few soft board books. If a first tooth has appeared, also get a soft infant toothbrush and begin gentle brushing twice daily; plan a first dental visit by age one.', 2),
(6, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Foods still on last month''s "hold off" list — honey, added salt/sugar, juice, tea, packaged baby snacks, whole grapes, nuts, and other choking hazards remain off-limits.', 0),
(6, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Cow''s milk as a main drink — still not until 12 months.', 1),
(6, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Worrying if baby is not crawling yet — the range is wide, and it is not a race. Avoid baby walkers because they are unsafe, and skip screens in favour of interaction and play.', 2),
(6, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Encourage safe floor time with sturdy, age-appropriate objects just out of reach to motivate movement, whatever form that takes for your baby. Avoid walkers and never leave baby unattended on an elevated surface.', 0),
(6, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue reading, talking, and responding to babbling — this "conversation" is real language building. Play simple games such as peek-a-boo and name everyday objects.', 1),
(6, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: this is a reasonable time to reassess your own activity level if you haven''t already found a rhythm that works.', 2),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine government vaccination visit is typically due this month; the next major one is usually around 9 completed months. Private or clinic schedules may differ, so follow baby''s immunisation card.', 0),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As mobility increases, recheck stairs, low cabinets, and anything newly within reach. Keep bathroom doors and water buckets inaccessible, and review window and balcony safety where relevant.', 1),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space.', 2),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Seek paediatric advice if baby seems unwell, has a fever lasting 5 days, is drinking or feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 3),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Also contact your paediatrician for persistent vomiting, signs of dehydration, or anything that genuinely worries you.', 4),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Layer clothing for outings and check warmth at the neck or chest, not hands or feet. For sleep, use clothing layers or a correctly sized sleeveless sleep sack — not loose blankets, quilts, hats, or weighted products.', 5),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Dry winter air can affect skin — moisturise as needed, especially after bathing, and use fragrance-free products if skin is sensitive.', 6),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Keep the home smoke-free and reasonably ventilated even with windows closed against cold. Avoid direct heater blasts near baby and watch for overheating.', 7),
(6, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Cold-and-flu season means extra caution with unwell visitors is still worthwhile. Encourage handwashing before anyone holds or feeds baby.', 8),
(7, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Crawling may become more established for some babies, but the range is genuinely wide. Scooting, rolling, bottom-shuffling, or taking longer are all common; some babies never crawl in the usual hands-and-knees way.', 0),
(7, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies may begin pulling to stand while holding stable furniture. Let baby lead; do not prop, pull, or force standing practice.', 1),
(7, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Stranger or separation anxiety commonly emerges around this age. Clinginess with familiar caregivers and wariness of new faces are normal; use a short, predictable goodbye and avoid forcing baby to be held by unfamiliar people.', 2),
(7, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Grasp is refining. Baby may rake small pieces of food with their fingers, transfer objects between hands, and explore everything by mouth — so keep small objects and choking hazards completely out of reach.', 3),
(7, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 4),
(7, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Separation anxiety can be emotionally taxing for you too. If childcare drop-offs or work separation feel harder than expected, that is a common temporary phase; a calm, predictable goodbye routine can help both of you.', 0),
(7, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months.', 1),
(7, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 2–3 small meals a day alongside regular breast milk or formula feeds. As baby approaches 9 months, gradually work towards 3 meals, with varied iron-rich foods and age-appropriate thicker textures.', 2),
(7, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as ever.', 3),
(7, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If baby is pulling to stand, anchor furniture and TVs urgently. Recheck low shelves, cabinets, cords, button batteries, magnets, plants, windows, balconies, and water buckets — new hazards become reachable quickly.', 0),
(7, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Choose simple stacking cups, blocks, or board books. If baby is already pulling up, a sturdy non-wheeled activity table can be useful; avoid wheeled baby walkers, which are unsafe.', 1),
(7, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer varied, iron-rich foods in safe textures. Sit baby upright in a high chair or on a stable lap, stay within arm''s reach throughout meals, and never feed while baby is reclining, in a stroller, or in a car seat.', 2),
(7, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep avoiding honey, added salt and sugar, juice, tea, cow''s milk as the main drink, and choking hazards such as whole nuts, whole grapes, hard raw pieces, popcorn, and hard sweets.', 0),
(7, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seated baby walkers with wheels — they are unsafe, not merely "not needed." Avoid them even with close supervision.', 1),
(7, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Trying to "fix" stranger anxiety or reading it as a problem. Offer comfort and gradual familiarity instead; never slip away without saying goodbye.', 2),
(7, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'If baby initiates pulling up, offer a clear, stable, low piece of furniture and stay nearby. Give plenty of safe floor time too; never force standing or cruising before baby is ready.', 0),
(7, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Play peek-a-boo and hide a toy partly under a cloth for baby to find. These simple games suit this stage as baby begins learning that people and objects still exist when out of sight.', 1),
(7, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever activity rhythm you''ve found; there''s no new expectation this month.', 2),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Book the 9-month government vaccination visit now and take baby''s immunisation card. Around 9 completed months, MR-1, a PCV booster where offered, vitamin A, and JE-1 in endemic areas may be due; follow your clinic''s schedule, as local and private schedules vary.', 0),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As baby pulls to stand or cruises, recheck furniture stability daily and clear new climbing hazards. Keep bathroom doors closed, water buckets inaccessible, and windows/balconies secured.', 1),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space. Do not use pillows, loose blankets, quilts, toys, positioners, or weighted products.', 2),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 3),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Also seek paediatric advice for persistent vomiting, markedly fewer wet diapers, or anything that feels seriously wrong to you.', 4),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Limited outdoor time does not mean limited activity — create a clear, warm indoor floor space for movement and play. Keep space heaters well away from baby and avoid overheating.', 5),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'If you use a humidifier for dry air, empty and dry it daily, clean it exactly as the manufacturer advises, and keep it out of baby''s reach.', 6),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Common colds are frequent in winter. Mild congestion or cough can often be watched when baby is feeding and breathing normally; use saline drops if advised, and do not give over-the-counter cough/cold medicines or honey without paediatric guidance.', 7),
(7, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Continue sensible hygiene with visitors, especially anyone who is unwell. Handwashing before holding or feeding baby is a simple, useful habit.', 8),
(8, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies may crawl, scoot, roll, bottom-shuffle, or begin cruising; others are still working towards mobility, and that is fine too. Movement styles and timing vary widely.', 0),
(8, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Hand skills are strengthening: baby may transfer objects between hands and rake small pieces of food with their fingers. A precise thumb-and-forefinger pincer grasp may be emerging, but is not expected for every baby yet.', 1),
(8, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies may pull to stand or cruise along stable furniture. Let baby lead; do not prop, pull, or force standing practice.', 2),
(8, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may look for a toy that is dropped or partly hidden, showing that objects still exist even when out of sight.', 3),
(8, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may lift their arms to be picked up or begin imitating a wave. Keep talking, singing, and responding to sounds and gestures.', 4),
(8, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 5),
(8, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you returned to work earlier in this journey, routines are often more settled by now, even if some days still feel chaotic.', 0),
(8, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Sleep patterns can still be unpredictable at this age — this isn''t a sign you''re doing something wrong.', 1),
(8, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months.', 2),
(8, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as month one.', 3),
(8, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'This is the month for baby''s 9-month vaccination visit — book it now if you have not already, and take the immunisation card with you.', 0),
(8, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied, iron-rich meals a day alongside regular breast milk or formula feeds. Use thicker mashed, finely chopped, or soft finger-food textures that baby can manage safely.', 1),
(8, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Reassess home safety as mobility and pulling to stand change what is within reach: anchor furniture and TVs; secure medicines, cleaners, small objects, button batteries, magnets, cords, windows, balconies, and water buckets.', 2),
(8, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep avoiding honey, added salt and sugar, juice, tea, cow''s milk as the main drink, and choking hazards such as whole nuts, whole grapes, hard raw pieces, popcorn, and hard sweets.', 0),
(8, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seated baby walkers with wheels — they are unsafe, not merely unnecessary. Avoid them even with close supervision.', 1),
(8, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Comparing crawling or standing timelines to other babies — the range here is genuinely wide.', 2),
(8, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Give plenty of safe floor time. If baby is already pulling up, offer stable low furniture and stay close; avoid forcing cruising. Choose a sturdy, non-wheeled activity table only if baby can already stand while holding on.', 0),
(8, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue reading, naming objects, repeating baby''s sounds, and responding to gestures. Play peek-a-boo, hide a toy partly under a cloth, and practise a simple wave during everyday goodbyes.', 1),
(8, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works; no new expectation this month.', 2),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Attend the 9-month visit and take baby''s immunisation card. Under the government schedule, MR-1, PCV booster, fIPV-3, and the first Vitamin A dose may be due; JE-1 is given in endemic areas. Your clinic will confirm the doses due locally and explain expected mild side effects.', 0),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space. Do not use pillows, loose blankets, quilts, toys, positioners, or weighted products.', 1),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 2),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As mobility increases, recheck furniture stability and newly reachable hazards. Also seek paediatric advice for persistent vomiting, markedly fewer wet diapers, or anything that feels seriously wrong to you.', 3),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Continue offering small supervised sips of safe water with meals, especially in hot weather. Breast milk or correctly prepared infant formula remains baby''s main drink.', 4),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Increased heat and activity can cause sweating and heat rash, especially in skin folds. Keep baby cool, dry, and in loose, breathable clothing.', 5),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Use shade, light clothing, and a hat for outdoor time; avoid peak heat where possible. Never leave baby in a parked vehicle, even briefly.', 6),
(8, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Watch for dehydration signs such as markedly fewer wet diapers, dry mouth, unusual sleepiness, or poor feeding. Seek paediatric advice promptly if you notice them.', 7),
(9, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies may pull to stand, cruise along furniture, or briefly stand with little support. Others are still crawling, scooting, or rolling — movement timing varies widely.', 0),
(9, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'First independent steps may happen near the first birthday or later. Walking independently at 10 months is not expected, and there is no need to hurry it.', 1),
(9, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Enjoy give-and-take games, naming familiar objects, and pairing words with gestures. Baby may respond to familiar routines, but following spoken instructions is still emerging and should not be expected yet.', 2),
(9, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may start showing clear preferences — reaching for a specific toy, refusing certain foods — this is a real personality developing, not stubbornness.', 3),
(9, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 4),
(9, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'A more mobile, opinionated baby often means a genuinely busier day — feeling more tired again isn''t a step backward, it''s a reasonable response to a real shift.', 0),
(9, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months.', 1),
(9, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Food preferences and occasional refusal are developmentally normal. Keep offering a rejected food calmly on other days; avoid pressure, force-feeding, or making a separate meal for every refusal.', 2),
(9, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as month one.', 3),
(9, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If baby is walking outdoors, choose closed-toe, comfortable, flexible shoes with non-slip soles and room for growth. Barefoot indoor play is fine; special arches, stiff ankle support, and "walking shoes" are not needed.', 0),
(9, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied, iron-rich meals a day alongside regular breast milk or formula feeds. Use soft, finely chopped, or mashed family-food textures that baby can manage safely, with no added salt or sugar.', 1),
(9, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Reassess babyproofing as standing and early steps change baby''s reach and range: anchor furniture and TVs; secure stairs, medicines, cleaners, small objects, button batteries, magnets, cords, windows, balconies, and water buckets.', 2),
(9, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep avoiding honey, added salt and sugar, juice, tea, cow''s milk as the main drink, and choking hazards such as whole nuts, whole grapes, hard raw pieces, popcorn, and hard sweets.', 0),
(9, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seated baby walkers with wheels — they remain unsafe even with close supervision. Also keep screens off-limits other than video calls with family.', 1),
(9, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Comparing walking timelines to other babies — the range here is genuinely wide, and early or late walking isn''t a predictor of anything on its own.', 2),
(9, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Give plenty of safe floor time and stable furniture for baby to use if they choose. Stay close, clear the path of hazards, and never force unsupported standing, cruising, or walking.', 0),
(9, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Play give-and-take, name familiar objects, repeat baby''s sounds, and use simple gestures in routines. Reading, singing, and hiding a toy partly under a cloth are still excellent play.', 1),
(9, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works.', 2),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine government vaccination visit is typically due this month; the next major one is usually around 16–24 months. Continue following baby''s immunisation card and paediatrician''s schedule, as private schedules may differ.', 0),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space. Do not use pillows, loose blankets, quilts, toys, positioners, or weighted products.', 1),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 2),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As mobility increases, recheck stairs, furniture edges, and every newly reachable hazard. Also seek paediatric advice for persistent vomiting, markedly fewer wet diapers, or anything that feels seriously wrong to you.', 3),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'For immediate emergencies — choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn — seek urgent medical help rather than waiting for the next clinic visit.', 4),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Continue offering small supervised sips of safe water with meals in hot weather; breast milk or correctly prepared infant formula remains baby''s main drink.', 5),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'More mobility means more sweating during play — watch for heat rash in skin folds and keep baby cool, dry, and in loose, breathable clothing.', 6),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Never leave baby in a parked vehicle, even briefly. In hot weather, prepare food fresh where possible; refrigerate promptly or discard leftovers rather than leaving food out.', 7),
(9, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Continue shade, breathable clothing, and avoiding peak heat for outdoor time. Watch for dehydration signs such as markedly fewer wet diapers, dry mouth, unusual sleepiness, or poor feeding.', 8),
(10, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Building on whatever movement style baby is using — cruising, early independent steps, or still primarily crawling or scooting — all can remain within the normal range this close to a year.', 0),
(10, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, '"Mama" or "dada" may begin to be used specifically for you, and baby may imitate a wave or pause when they hear "no." These skills vary, and some babies establish them a little later.', 1),
(10, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may start showing or reaching toward things of interest, deliberately drop objects to watch what happens, and enjoy simple cause-and-effect play. This is real learning, not mischief.', 2),
(10, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may look for a familiar toy hidden under a cloth and enjoy putting objects into a cup or container. Repeat the game and celebrate the attempt rather than making it a test.', 3),
(10, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 4),
(10, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Approaching baby''s first birthday can bring up real emotion — reflecting on the year doesn''t have to be uniformly happy, and mixed feelings are normal too.', 0),
(10, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months.', 1),
(10, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you''re thinking ahead about family planning or spacing, this is a reasonable time to raise it with your doctor if you haven''t already.', 2),
(10, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as month one.', 3),
(10, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you are planning anything for baby''s first birthday, keep it simple and safety-led. Avoid balloons, small party favours, hard sweets, popcorn, and unsupervised eating; keep candles and hot drinks well out of reach.', 0),
(10, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied, iron-rich meals a day alongside regular breast milk or formula feeds; 1–2 nutritious snacks can be offered if wanted. Continue soft, finely chopped, or mashed family-food textures and responsive, pressure-free feeding.', 1),
(10, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Reassess safety once more as baby moves faster: anchor furniture and TVs; secure stairs, medicines, cleaners, small objects, button batteries, magnets, cords, windows, balconies, and water buckets.', 2),
(10, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Honey and cow''s milk as the main drink still wait until 12 months. Keep breast milk or correctly prepared infant formula as the main milk drink for this final pre-birthday month.', 0),
(10, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep avoiding added salt and sugar, juice, tea, and choking hazards such as whole nuts, whole grapes, hard raw pieces, popcorn, and hard sweets.', 1),
(10, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seated baby walkers with wheels and screens other than video calls — still off-limits.', 2),
(10, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe floor, crawling, and cruising space; there is no need to push walking practice. Let baby lead and keep a clear, stable path for any self-initiated movement.', 0),
(10, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple cause-and-effect toys — stacking, nesting, dropping, and putting objects into containers — suit this stage well. If teeth are present, brush twice daily with a tiny smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a first dental visit by age one.', 1),
(10, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works.', 2),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine government vaccination visit is typically due this month — the next major one remains around 16–24 months. Follow baby''s immunisation card and paediatrician''s schedule, as private schedules may differ.', 0),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space. Do not use pillows, loose blankets, quilts, toys, positioners, or weighted products.', 1),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 2),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'For immediate emergencies — choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn — seek urgent medical help rather than waiting for a clinic visit.', 3),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As mobility and speed increase, recheck hazards once more. Also seek paediatric advice for persistent vomiting, markedly fewer wet diapers, or anything that feels seriously wrong to you.', 4),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Wet, slippery floors near entryways raise fall risk — keep these areas dry, wiped down, and free of loose mats or clutter.', 5),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue mosquito protection as baby''s outdoor curiosity grows, and clear standing water around the home where possible.', 6),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Food hygiene remains important as family-food variety expands: use safe drinking water, cook thoroughly, use clean prep surfaces, refrigerate promptly, and discard leftovers that have been left out.', 7),
(10, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue reasonable caution with unwell visitors as illness circulates more in this season. Handwashing before holding or feeding baby remains a simple, useful habit.', 8),
(11, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies may be walking independently; others may be pulling to stand or cruising along furniture. Independent walking is not required at 12 months — speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills or a concern about development.', 0),
(11, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may call a parent "mama" or "dada" (or another special name), wave bye-bye, or pause briefly when they hear "no." Skills develop at different speeds.', 1),
(11, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Practise small sips from an open cup with help; spilling is normal. A straw cup can be another useful way to practise drinking without a bottle.', 2),
(11, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may enjoy pat-a-cake, putting blocks into a cup, looking for a toy hidden under a cloth, and turning pages in a picture book.', 3),
(11, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age — this note remains relevant even at the one-year mark.', 4),
(11, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'The first year is a genuine milestone worth acknowledging for yourself too, not just baby — however you''re feeling about it, however messy or smooth this year actually was.', 0),
(11, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months — the first year ending doesn''t mean postpartum mood changes can''t still emerge or persist.', 1),
(11, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If breastfeeding continues to work for you both past a year, that is entirely fine to continue; if you are weaning, that is equally fine. WHO supports breastfeeding to two years or beyond if mother and child wish.', 2),
(11, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as month one.', 3),
(11, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'After the first birthday, pasteurised whole cow''s milk can be offered if baby is not breastfeeding. An India-specific guide for ages 1–3 is about 300 ml a day (two 150 ml servings) within a varied diet; needs vary, so check with your paediatrician if growth, appetite, allergy, or diet is a concern.', 0),
(11, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep practising open or straw cups and gradually phase bottles out rather than stopping abruptly. Offer water with meals; serve milk in a cup where possible.', 1),
(11, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Toddler-appropriate toys — blocks, simple puzzles, push-along toys, picture books, and pretend-play basics — suit this stage well. Choose sturdy, age-appropriate items without small detachable parts.', 2),
(11, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, and other choking hazards remain unsafe well past age one. Modify food shape and texture, and stay within arm''s reach while eating.', 0),
(11, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep limiting added salt and sugar, juice, and tea as the diet expands. Aim for varied family foods, chopped or mashed as needed.', 1),
(11, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Screens — regular screen time is still discouraged at this age, aside from video calls with loved ones.', 2),
(11, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Provide a clear, safe space for self-led walking, cruising, or crawling. Let baby hold stable furniture and explore at their own pace; never use seated baby walkers with wheels.', 0),
(11, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Play pat-a-cake, read picture books, put blocks into containers, and name everyday objects. These simple games build connection, hand skills, and language.', 1),
(11, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works — there''s no new expectation tied to the birthday itself.', 2),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine government vaccination visit is specifically due at 12 months — the next major one remains around 16–24 months. Follow baby''s immunisation card and paediatrician''s schedule, as private schedules may differ.', 0),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If not already done, this is a good checkpoint for baby''s first dental visit. If teeth are present, brush twice daily with a tiny smear of fluoride toothpaste.', 1),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat surface with nothing else in the sleep space. Do not use pillows, loose blankets, quilts, toys, positioners, or weighted products.', 2),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 3),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'As mobility grows, recheck home safety once more. For immediate emergencies — choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn — seek urgent medical help; also seek advice for persistent vomiting or markedly fewer wet diapers.', 4),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Wet, slippery floors near entryways raise fall risk — keep these areas dry, wiped down, and free of loose mats or clutter.', 5),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue mosquito protection and clear standing water around the home where possible. Food hygiene remains important: use safe drinking water, cook thoroughly, use clean prep surfaces, refrigerate promptly, and discard leftovers that have been left out.', 6),
(11, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue reasonable caution with unwell visitors through the season. Handwashing before holding or feeding baby remains a simple, useful habit.', 7),
(12, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies may be taking early independent steps; others cruise along furniture, crawl, or scoot. All can be normal at this stage. There is no need to rush walking, but speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills or a developmental concern.', 0),
(12, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may respond to their name, a familiar routine, or a familiar object you name. Understanding often grows before speech. Pair a simple request with a gesture and give baby time to respond.', 1),
(12, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some babies may begin using a word or two beyond "mama" or "dada"; gestures, pointing, sounds, and eye contact are communication too. These skills vary widely and are not expected on a fixed Month 13 timeline.', 2),
(12, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Self-feeding with fingers is often well-established now; offer a toddler-safe spoon and let baby practise, even when it is messy. Sitting upright and staying within arm''s reach during meals keeps practice safer.', 3),
(12, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 4),
(12, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Life past the first birthday often settles into its own rhythm, though "settled" looks different for every family.', 0),
(12, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same mood warning signs as previous months — this remains just as relevant past the one-year mark.', 1),
(12, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'If you''re adjusting to a new phase now that infancy has technically ended, mixed feelings about that transition are normal too.', 2),
(12, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as ever.', 3),
(12, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A toddler-safe spoon and an open or straw cup, if not already in regular use. If teeth are present, use a soft toothbrush twice daily with a tiny smear of fluoride toothpaste.', 0),
(12, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks, according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; continue breastfeeding if you both wish. If baby is not breastfeeding, pasteurised whole cow''s milk can be part of the diet — roughly 300 ml a day is an India-specific guide for ages 1–3, without letting milk crowd out meals.', 1),
(12, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Do one more babyproofing pass as speed, reach, and curiosity grow: anchor furniture and TVs; secure stairs, windows/balconies, cords, medicines and cleaners; keep button batteries, magnets, and small objects out of reach; and supervise around water.', 2),
(12, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, and other choking hazards remain unsafe. Modify food shape and texture, and stay within arm''s reach while baby eats.', 0),
(12, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Screens are still discouraged at this age, aside from occasional video calls. Continue limiting added salt and sugar, juice, and tea as family foods expand.', 1),
(12, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any pressure around walking timelines — the range remains wide well past 13 months.', 2),
(12, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep a clear, safe space for whatever movement stage baby is in. Let them explore at their own pace — no rush toward walking and no seated baby walkers with wheels.', 0),
(12, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple container and stacking play, picture books, and naming everyday objects remain excellent. Follow baby''s interest rather than needing a particular toy or outcome.', 1),
(12, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works.', 2),
(12, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine government vaccination visit is specifically due this month; the next major one is generally between 16 and 24 months. Follow baby''s immunisation card and paediatrician''s schedule, as private schedules may differ.', 0),
(12, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: place baby on their back for every sleep, on a firm, flat sleep surface with nothing else in the sleep space. Do not use pillows, loose blankets, quilts, toys, positioners, or weighted products.', 1),
(12, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, or a rash that does not fade when pressed.', 2),
(12, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If baby''s first dental visit has not happened yet, this remains a good time to arrange it. For immediate emergencies — choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn — seek urgent medical help.', 3),
(12, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Dress baby in light layers and check warmth at the neck or chest, not hands or feet. Avoid bulky coats under a car-seat harness.', 4),
(12, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Indoor floor space for movement matters when outdoor time is limited. For sleep, do not add loose quilts, pillows, or hats; keep heaters safely away from baby and avoid overheating the room.', 5),
(12, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Cold-and-flu season caution with visitors remains worthwhile. Ask anyone who is unwell to postpone visiting, and keep handwashing before feeding or holding baby a simple routine.', 6),
(13, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some toddlers may be taking a few independent steps; others are still cruising, crawling, or just beginning. There is no need to rush walking. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills or a developmental concern.', 0),
(13, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple gestures may be building — shaking the head "no," waving, pointing to ask for help or share interest, or looking toward a familiar object you name. These skills develop at different speeds.', 1),
(13, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may try to use familiar objects in the right way, such as holding a toy phone to their ear, looking at a book, or using a cup. This kind of imitation is encouraging, but it is still emerging rather than required at a fixed Month 14 timeline.', 2),
(13, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Drinking from an open cup with spilling, and messy spoon practice, both remain normal. Let baby practise while sitting upright and stay within arm''s reach during meals.', 3),
(13, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 4),
(13, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Managing an increasingly mobile toddler can bring back a kind of tiredness that feels different from early infancy — that''s a reasonable response to real physical demands, not a step backward.', 0),
(13, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Alongside rest, notice persistent low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, or intrusive thoughts. Tell a trusted person and seek professional support promptly if these feel overwhelming; seek urgent help if there is any risk of harm to yourself or baby.', 1),
(13, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as ever.', 2),
(13, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue toddler-safe utensils and open/straw cups in regular use. If teeth are present, brush twice daily with a tiny smear of fluoride toothpaste; arrange the first dental visit if it has not happened yet.', 0),
(13, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks, according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; continue breastfeeding if you both wish. If baby is not breastfeeding, pasteurised whole cow''s milk can be part of the diet — roughly 300 ml a day is an India-specific guide for ages 1–3, without letting milk crowd out meals.', 1),
(13, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Do one more babyproofing pass as speed, reach, and climbing change: anchor furniture and TVs; secure stairs and windows/balconies; keep cords, medicines, cleaners, button batteries, magnets, and small objects out of reach; and supervise around water.', 2),
(13, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, and other choking hazards remain unsafe. Modify food shape and texture, and stay within arm''s reach while baby eats. Screens are still discouraged at this age, aside from occasional video calls.', 0),
(13, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any pressure around walking or talking timelines — the range remains wide. Use baby''s progress over time, and ask your paediatrician if you are concerned rather than comparing with other children.', 1),
(13, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue a clear, safe space for whatever movement stage baby is in, following their pace. Avoid seated baby walkers with wheels.', 0),
(13, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple pretend-play props — a toy phone, a spoon for "stirring," a doll, or blocks — suit this stage if baby shows interest. Read, name everyday objects, and follow their lead; there is no need to prompt a performance.', 1),
(13, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works.', 2),
(13, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine government vaccination visit is specifically due this month. The next major visit is generally between 16 and 24 months; follow baby''s immunisation card and paediatrician''s schedule, as private schedules may differ. Vitamin A may also be due from around 16 months.', 0),
(13, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep a safe sleep space: use a firm, appropriate cot or bed surface and avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. Check that the sleep space is in good repair and free of cords or gaps where baby could become trapped.', 1),
(13, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, a rash that does not fade when pressed, choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn.', 2),
(13, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'For cold floors or outdoor time, choose well-fitting, flexible footwear with a grippy sole. Bare feet are also fine on clean, dry, familiar indoor surfaces when an adult is supervising.', 3),
(13, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Dry winter air can worsen skin dryness — continue moisturising. If using a humidifier, empty and dry it daily, clean it as directed by the manufacturer, and keep it out of baby''s reach.', 4),
(13, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Reduced winter sun exposure is normal. Ask your paediatrician whether vitamin D supplementation is relevant for your child specifically; do not start a supplement without their guidance.', 5),
(13, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Common winter illnesses circulate more now. Ask unwell visitors to postpone, practise handwashing before feeding or holding baby, and use the fever and breathing-difficulty red flags rather than assuming any cough or cold is automatically minor.', 6),
(14, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some toddlers may be taking a few independent steps; others are still cruising, crawling, or just beginning. There is no need to rush walking. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills or a developmental concern.', 0),
(14, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may try to say one or two words besides "mama" or "dada," and may point to ask for help or to share interest. These skills develop at different speeds.', 1),
(14, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may try to use familiar objects in the right way — drinking from a cup, looking at a book, or holding a toy phone to their ear.', 2),
(14, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple directions are often easiest to follow when you use both a gesture and words, such as holding out your hand while saying, "Give me the toy." Give baby time to respond.', 3),
(14, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may show affection through hugs, cuddles, or kisses. Stacking two small objects, pointing games, and copying everyday actions are all lovely ways to play together.', 4),
(14, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 5),
(14, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'A newly walking, more independent toddler often means chasing and redirecting more than earlier months — genuinely tiring in a different way.', 0),
(14, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Notice persistent low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, or intrusive thoughts. Tell a trusted person and seek professional support promptly if these feel overwhelming; seek urgent help if there is any risk of harm to yourself or baby.', 1),
(14, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as ever.', 2),
(14, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'For outdoor walking, choose well-fitting, flexible shoes with a grippy sole. Bare feet are fine on clean, dry, familiar indoor surfaces when an adult is supervising.', 0),
(14, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks, according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; continue breastfeeding if you both wish. If baby is not breastfeeding, pasteurised whole cow''s milk can be part of the diet — roughly 300 ml a day is an India-specific guide for ages 1–3, without letting milk crowd out meals.', 1),
(14, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Do one more babyproofing pass as walking and climbing change: anchor furniture and TVs; secure stairs and windows/balconies; keep cords, medicines, cleaners, button batteries, magnets, and small objects out of reach; and supervise around water.', 2),
(14, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, and other choking hazards remain unsafe. Modify food shape and texture, and stay within arm''s reach while baby eats. Screens are still discouraged at this age, aside from occasional video calls; continue limiting added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(14, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Comparing walking or talking timelines to other toddlers — the range remains wide. Use baby''s progress over time, and ask your paediatrician if you are concerned rather than comparing with other children.', 1),
(14, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Encourage walking and exploring on safe, even surfaces. Use gates and close supervision around stairs, and avoid seated baby walkers with wheels.', 0),
(14, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple stacking, pointing games, picture books, and naming everyday objects remain excellent. Follow baby''s interest and let play stay playful.', 1),
(14, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works.', 2),
(14, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine government vaccination visit is specifically due this month, but the 16–24-month visit is next. Check baby''s immunisation card and paediatrician''s schedule, as private schedules may differ; Vitamin A may also be due from around 16 months.', 0),
(14, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep a safe sleep space: use a firm, appropriate cot or bed surface and avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. If teeth are present, brush twice daily with a tiny smear of fluoride toothpaste; arrange the first dental visit if it has not happened yet.', 1),
(14, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, a rash that does not fade when pressed, choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn.', 2),
(14, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'For outdoor play, seek shade and use lightweight covering clothing and a brimmed hat. Avoid the strongest sun, roughly 10 am–4 pm, and use sunscreen on exposed skin as directed for your child.', 3),
(14, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Offer water with meals and frequent small sips during active outdoor play. Toddlers may not remember to drink or take a shade break, so an adult needs to offer both.', 4),
(14, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Watch for heat rash, unusual tiredness, weakness, or irritability during hot play. Move baby to a cool, shaded place and offer water if heat seems to be affecting them; get medical advice if you are worried.', 5),
(14, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Never leave baby in a parked vehicle, even briefly — temperatures inside can become dangerous quickly, even with windows open.', 6),
(15, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Walking may become steadier and more confident, while running and more complex movement are still developing. There is no need to rush. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills or a developmental concern.', 0),
(15, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some toddlers may add more sounds or single words; others still communicate mainly through gestures, pointing, and expression. Vocabulary grows at different speeds in this stretch.', 1),
(15, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Big emotional reactions may start appearing as toddlers want more than they can yet express or manage. This is a normal developmental stage, not a discipline problem or something gone wrong.', 2),
(15, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some toddlers may enjoy making marks with large, non-toxic, toddler-safe crayons. Offer them with close supervision; scribbling is an emerging interest, not a skill to test.', 3),
(15, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 4),
(15, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'The first tantrums can be genuinely jarring — they''re a normal part of this stage, not a sign of a "difficult" child or a parenting failure.', 0),
(15, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Notice persistent low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, or intrusive thoughts. Tell a trusted person and seek professional support promptly if these feel overwhelming; seek urgent help if there is any risk of harm to yourself or baby.', 1),
(15, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as ever.', 2),
(15, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Large, non-toxic, toddler-safe crayons and paper, if introducing early mark-making. Avoid small or broken pieces, and stay nearby while baby uses them.', 0),
(15, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks, according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; continue breastfeeding if you both wish. If baby is not breastfeeding, pasteurised whole cow''s milk can be part of the diet — roughly 300 ml a day is an India-specific guide for ages 1–3, without letting milk crowd out meals.', 1),
(15, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'For pool time or summer travel, plan water safety now: identify who will provide uninterrupted touch supervision, check pool gates/fences and bathroom access, and keep life jackets appropriate for the activity. Floats and swim lessons never replace adult supervision.', 2),
(15, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, and other choking hazards remain unsafe. Modify food shape and texture, and stay within arm''s reach while baby eats. Screens are still discouraged at this age, aside from occasional video calls; continue limiting added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(15, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any pressure around vocabulary or walking — the range remains wide. Use baby''s progress over time, and ask your paediatrician if you are concerned rather than comparing with other children.', 1),
(15, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue walking and exploring on safe surfaces; climbing curiosity often grows alongside confidence. Use gates and close supervision around stairs, and avoid seated baby walkers with wheels.', 0),
(15, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple scribbling, stacking, pointing games, picture books, and naming everyday objects are excellent play. During a tantrum, stay calm, keep baby safe, use few words, and offer comfort or a quiet pause once the wave passes.', 1),
(15, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works.', 2),
(15, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'The government immunisation window is open now. Check baby''s card and book or attend the 16–24-month visit: it commonly includes DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster; JE 2 applies in relevant areas. Vitamin A is generally due around 16–18 months. Private schedules may differ, so confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(15, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep a safe sleep space: use a firm, appropriate cot or bed surface and avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. If teeth are present, brush twice daily with a tiny smear of fluoride toothpaste; arrange the first dental visit if it has not happened yet.', 1),
(15, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, a rash that does not fade when pressed, choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn.', 2),
(15, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Toddlers can drown quickly and silently in very small amounts of water. In or near any water — pools, bathtubs, buckets, ponds, or large containers — a capable adult should stay within arm''s reach and give full attention ("touch supervision").', 3),
(15, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Never leave baby alone near water, even briefly, and never rely on another child to supervise. During pool time, the supervising adult should be in the water with a toddler; floats and swim lessons do not make a child water-safe.', 4),
(15, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Empty buckets and containers immediately after use; keep bathroom doors closed or latched when not supervising. For a home pool, use a secure four-sided fence with a self-latching gate.', 5),
(15, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'For outdoor summer play, seek shade; use lightweight covering clothing and a brimmed hat; avoid the strongest sun, roughly 10 am–4 pm; and use sunscreen on exposed skin as directed. Offer frequent water sips and shade breaks, watch for heat rash or unusual tiredness, and never leave baby in a parked vehicle.', 6),
(16, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Walking may keep becoming more confident, while running, climbing, and more complex movement continue to develop at each toddler''s own pace. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills or a developmental concern.', 0),
(16, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some toddlers may add new sounds or attempt a few more words; others still communicate mainly through gestures and pointing. Both can be within the wide normal range at this stage.', 1),
(16, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Big emotional reactions may continue as toddlers want more than they can yet express or manage. This remains a normal part of development, not something gone wrong.', 2),
(16, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Some toddlers may show early interest in copying everyday actions or simple pretend play. Follow their lead — it is emerging, not something to expect on a fixed timeline.', 3),
(16, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age.', 4),
(16, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Managing tantrums repeatedly can be genuinely draining. Needing a break afterward is a reasonable response, not impatience; share the load where possible and keep asking for help when you need it.', 0),
(16, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Notice persistent low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, or intrusive thoughts. Tell a trusted person and seek professional support promptly if these feel overwhelming; seek urgent help if there is any risk of harm to yourself or baby.', 1),
(16, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest and self-care remain as valid a priority as ever.', 2),
(16, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If the 16–24-month vaccination visit is not yet done, book it now and keep baby''s immunisation card ready. Recheck toddler safety too: anchor furniture and TVs; secure stairs and windows/balconies; and keep medicines, cleaners, button batteries, magnets, and small objects out of reach.', 0),
(16, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks, according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; continue breastfeeding if you both wish. If baby is not breastfeeding, pasteurised whole cow''s milk can be part of the diet — roughly 300 ml a day is an India-specific guide for ages 1–3, without letting milk crowd out meals. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 1),
(16, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple pretend-play props, if baby shows interest — a toy kitchen item, a doll, or a play phone. Nothing elaborate is needed; sturdy, age-appropriate items without small detachable parts are best.', 2),
(16, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, and other choking hazards remain unsafe. Modify food shape and texture, and stay within arm''s reach while baby eats. Screens are still discouraged at this age, aside from occasional video calls; continue limiting added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(16, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any pressure around vocabulary, walking, or emotional-regulation timelines — the range remains wide through this whole stretch. Ask your paediatrician if you have a specific concern rather than comparing with other toddlers.', 1),
(16, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue walking and safe climbing exploration with close supervision. Use gates around stairs, and avoid seated baby walkers with wheels.', 0),
(16, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'During a tantrum, stay calm, keep baby safe, use few words, and offer comfort or a quiet pause once the wave passes. Consistent, loving limits help more than trying to reason in the middle of a big feeling.', 1),
(16, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever rhythm works.', 2),
(16, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If not already done, attend the 16–24-month government visit: DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due, with JE 2 in relevant areas and Vitamin A generally around 16–18 months. Private schedules may differ, so check baby''s card and confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(16, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep a safe sleep space: firm, appropriate surface, no heavy loose bedding, pillows, or overheating. If teeth are present, brush twice daily with a tiny smear of fluoride toothpaste; arrange the first dental visit if it hasn''t happened yet.', 1),
(16, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'A fever is usually 38°C or above. Contact your paediatrician if fever lasts 5 days, baby is feeding poorly, or you are worried. Get urgent help for breathing difficulty, unusual sleepiness, seizures, dehydration signs, a rash that does not fade when pressed, choking, suspected poisoning, a serious fall, or a burn.', 2),
(16, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Wet floors and loose mats raise fall risk as baby walks and climbs — keep frequently used areas dry, wipe spills promptly, and secure or remove loose mats and slippery entryways.', 3),
(16, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue mosquito protection: remove standing water around the home, use screens/nets where practical, and use child-safe repellent only as directed on its label.', 4),
(16, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Food hygiene remains important as toddler food variety expands — use safe drinking water, cook thoroughly, keep preparation surfaces clean, refrigerate promptly, and discard food left out too long.', 5),
(16, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Continue reasonable caution with unwell visitors through the season. Handwashing before feeding or holding baby remains a simple, useful habit.', 6),
(17, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Walking without holding on is well-established for many toddlers. Running and climbing continue to develop at each child''s own pace; supervise climbing and make the space safe.', 0),
(17, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may point to show you something interesting, follow a familiar one-step instruction without a gesture, help with dressing, or hold hands out to be washed. These skills appear across a wide range of timing.', 1),
(17, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may try three or more words besides "mama" or "dada", copy a simple household action, or play with a toy in a simple way. Gestures remain an important and valid form of communication.', 2),
(17, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Trying a spoon, finger-feeding, scribbling, and drinking from an open cup are all useful practice now — spills and mess are still completely normal.', 3),
(17, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills, a concern about communication, or any developmental question.', 4),
(17, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Independence-seeking often intensifies around 18 months — more "no", more testing of limits, and big feelings. This is a normal developmental push, not defiance aimed at you personally. Gentle, consistent limits and connection both help.', 0),
(17, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Your wellbeing matters too. Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(17, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities. Asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
(17, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'If the 16–24-month vaccination visit is still pending, book or complete it now. Take baby''s immunisation card and use the visit to review growth, feeding, sleep, development, and any concerns.', 0),
(17, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A toddler spoon and fork suited to independent self-feeding, if not already in use. Keep dental basics stocked too: a small soft brush and a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste twice daily.', 1),
(17, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; water with meals; and continued breastfeeding if you both wish. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 2),
(17, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and continue avoiding routine screen use, added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(17, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pressure to tick off every skill this month. The range is genuinely wide even at this checkpoint; focus on progress, connection, and discussing questions early with your paediatrician.', 1),
(17, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Make room each day for walking, early running, and supervised climbing on safe surfaces. Secure stairs, windows/balconies, furniture, and TVs; avoid seated wheeled walkers.', 0),
(17, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple body-part naming, pointing games, picture books, copying everyday actions, scribbling, and turn-taking sounds or words suit this stage well. Follow baby''s interest rather than drilling skills.', 1),
(17, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(17, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'At the 16–24-month public-service visit, DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due; JE 2 applies in relevant areas, and Vitamin A may also be due. Private schedules can differ, so check the card with your paediatrician. At the 18-month check, ask about routine developmental and autism-specific screening.', 0),
(17, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep: use a firm, age-appropriate cot or bed and avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. Keep brushing teeth twice daily and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(17, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(17, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Avoid floodwater and puddle water where practical. Wash hands and feet after outdoor play, keep cuts clean and covered, and use safe drinking water and hygienically prepared food. Seek medical advice promptly for persistent diarrhoea, blood in stool, poor drinking, or unusual sleepiness.', 3),
(17, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Choose quick-drying, non-slip footwear for outdoor exploration and dry feet thoroughly afterward. Keep clothing and bedding fully dry before use to help prevent skin irritation and fungal rashes.', 4),
(17, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Reduce mosquito breeding by emptying standing water around the home. Use screens or nets where practical, and child-safe repellent only as directed on its label.', 5),
(18, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Walking and early running are well-established for many toddlers. Some may begin walking up a few steps with help or a rail; coming down usually takes longer. Stay close, use stair gates where needed, and keep stairs clear and dry.', 0),
(18, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Vocabulary may begin expanding more noticeably now, though the range stays wide. Support language through everyday back-and-forth: name what baby points to, pause for a response, read together, and gently add a word or two — without testing or correcting.', 1),
(18, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple pretend play may deepen — feeding a doll, pretending to talk on a toy phone, or pushing a toy car with sound. Join in when invited and let baby lead the story.', 2),
(18, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'A playful two-action routine, such as "pick up your cup, then put it on the table," may start to make sense in familiar situations. Keep it light; this skill is still developing toward the two-year stage.', 3),
(18, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills, a concern about communication, or any developmental question.', 4),
(18, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Toddler independence and testing continue. Consistency in gentle limits tends to help more than any single "right" response in the moment; name the feeling, keep the boundary, and reconnect once the storm has passed.', 0),
(18, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Your wellbeing matters too. Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(18, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities. Asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
(18, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; water with meals; and continued breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet, but should not crowd out meals. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 0),
(18, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple picture books with clear, detailed pictures suit growing attention and language now. Re-reading favourites, pointing, and chatting about what baby notices all count.', 1),
(18, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A sturdy, non-slip step stool for hand-washing, if helpful. Stay beside toddler around water; never leave them alone in the bathroom, even briefly.', 2),
(18, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and continue avoiding routine screen use, added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(18, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pressure around vocabulary size or skill timing. The range stays genuinely wide toward the two-year mark; focus on progress, connection, and discussing questions early with your paediatrician.', 1),
(18, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue walking, running, and supervised stair practice. Secure stairs, windows/balconies, furniture, and TVs; remove loose mats and keep walkways dry. Avoid seated wheeled walkers.', 0),
(18, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple pretend play, stacking, picture books, scribbling, and ball play remain excellent. Use real-life language during play: "car goes fast," "doll is sleepy," then pause to let baby respond.', 1),
(18, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(18, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If the 16–24-month vaccination visit is still pending, complete it now and take baby''s immunisation card. DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due; JE 2 applies in relevant areas, and Vitamin A may also be due. Private schedules can differ, so confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(18, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep with a firm, age-appropriate cot or bed; avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. Keep brushing teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(18, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(18, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Use light layers and check baby''s chest or back for warmth rather than hands and feet. Avoid bulky coats under a car-seat harness, and keep room heaters, hot drinks, and hot-water sources safely out of reach. Avoid direct heat and smoke exposure.', 3),
(18, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Dry winter air can affect skin — moisturise regularly. If using a humidifier, clean and dry it daily as directed, and avoid making the room overly warm.', 4),
(18, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Cold-and-flu season caution with unwell visitors remains worthwhile. Handwashing before meals and after outside play is useful as toddler touches more surfaces; keep routine vaccinations up to date.', 5),
(19, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Walking, running, and climbing continue growing more confident. Kicking or throwing a light, soft ball may begin, though coordination is still developing; keep ball play away from roads, stairs, glass, and other children''s faces.', 0),
(19, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Vocabulary may keep building gradually. Some toddlers may begin combining two words, such as "more milk" or "bye dada," though many are not there yet and that can still be within the normal range. Describe what baby is doing, pause, and respond to gestures or words rather than testing vocabulary.', 1),
(19, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Imitation deepens — copying household tasks like sweeping, wiping, or "cooking" is a real sign of learning through watching you. Let baby help with simple safe tasks and name what you are doing together.', 2),
(19, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may have stronger preferences and big reactions when a wish cannot happen. Offer two simple choices where possible, hold gentle limits, and reconnect afterward.', 3),
(19, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills, a concern about communication, or any developmental question.', 4),
(19, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'The push-and-pull of toddler independence can be genuinely tiring. A strong reaction from baby is not a reflection of your parenting; calm, consistent limits and repair afterward are enough.', 0),
(19, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Your wellbeing matters too. Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(19, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities. Asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
(19, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; water with meals; and continued breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet, but should not crowd out meals. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 0),
(19, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'A lightweight, soft ball for kicking and throwing practice suits this stage well. Keep it large enough not to be a choking hazard and use it in a clear, safe play space.', 1),
(19, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Sturdy board books that invite participation, such as lift-the-flap or texture books, suit growing engagement. Choose age-appropriate books without loose or detachable small parts.', 2),
(19, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and continue avoiding routine screen use, added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(19, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pressure around word combinations or specific skills. The range stays genuinely wide toward the two-year mark; focus on progress, connection, and discussing questions early with your paediatrician.', 1),
(19, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe active play — walking, running, ball play, supervised climbing, and stairs. Secure stairs, windows/balconies, furniture, and TVs; remove loose mats and keep walkways dry. Avoid seated wheeled walkers.', 0),
(19, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Imitation play — letting baby "help" with simple safe tasks — supports learning and connection. Picture books, scribbling, stacking, and simple ball games are all excellent too.', 1),
(19, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(19, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If the 16–24-month vaccination visit is still pending, complete it now and take baby''s immunisation card. DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due; JE 2 applies in relevant areas, and Vitamin A may also be due. Private schedules can differ, so confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(19, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep with a firm, age-appropriate cot or bed; avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. Keep brushing teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(19, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(19, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'As a more mobile toddler explores, winter burn risks grow: use active barriers around space heaters and cooking areas, keep hot beverages and hot-water sources out of reach, check bath water first, and avoid direct heater heat and smoke exposure.', 3),
(19, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Use light layers that allow free movement. Check baby''s chest or back for warmth rather than hands and feet, and remove a layer if they seem overheated.', 4),
(19, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Continue winter illness precautions: encourage handwashing before meals and after outside play, keep distance from clearly unwell visitors where possible, and keep routine vaccinations up to date.', 5),
(20, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Running may look more coordinated now. Some toddlers may be more confident walking up a few stairs with help or a rail, though coming down remains harder and needs close supervision. Keep stairs clear and dry, and use gates where needed.', 0),
(20, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Two-word combinations may be emerging for some toddlers; vocabulary size still varies widely, and gestures plus a few clear words remain valid communication. Support language by responding to what baby points to or says, adding a word or two, and pausing for their turn — without testing.', 1),
(20, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Sorting or matching simple shapes or colours may interest some toddlers, though this is emerging, not expected. Match objects in daily life and name colours or shapes casually; let baby lead rather than drilling.', 2),
(20, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may show clearer pretend sequences — putting a doll to "sleep," then covering it — reflecting growing imagination and memory. Join in when invited and follow baby''s story.', 3),
(20, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills, a concern about communication, or any developmental question.', 4),
(20, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Big toddler emotions often peak somewhere in this stretch. Offering simple choices within firm limits tends to help more than reasoning in the heat of a meltdown; name the feeling, keep the boundary, and reconnect afterward.', 0),
(20, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Your wellbeing matters too. Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(20, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities. Asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
(20, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; water with and between meals; and continued breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet, but should not crowd out meals. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 0),
(20, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple sorting or shape toys, if introducing them, can suit growing interest. Choose sturdy pieces too large to swallow and without loose magnets, button batteries, or detachable small parts.', 1),
(20, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Lightweight summer clothing and a broad-brimmed sun hat can make outdoor time more comfortable. Choose breathable fabrics and keep a spare set for sweaty play.', 2),
(20, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and continue avoiding routine screen use, added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(20, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pressure around word combinations or specific skills. The range stays genuinely wide toward the two-year mark; focus on progress, connection, and discussing questions early with your paediatrician.', 1),
(20, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe active play — running, ball play, supervised climbing, and stairs. Secure stairs, windows/balconies, furniture, and TVs; remove loose mats and keep walkways dry. Avoid seated wheeled walkers.', 0),
(20, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple pretend sequences, sorting, picture books, scribbling, and ball games suit this stage well. Keep play short, shared, and fun rather than turning it into a lesson.', 1),
(20, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(20, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If the 16–24-month vaccination visit is still pending, complete it now and take baby''s immunisation card. DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due; JE 2 applies in relevant areas, and Vitamin A may also be due. Private schedules can differ, so confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(20, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep with a firm, age-appropriate cot or bed; avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. Keep brushing teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(20, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(20, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'A faster, more independent toddler plus summer water means close, constant touch supervision matters. Pools, buckets, open containers, and bathtubs all need an adult within arm''s reach. Empty buckets and open containers immediately after use, and block unsupervised access to bathrooms and pools.', 3),
(20, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Offer water with and between meals and after active outdoor play; a busy toddler may not ask. Choose water rather than sweet drinks, and watch for signs of overheating such as unusual tiredness, irritability, or very warm skin.', 4),
(20, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Use shade, light clothing, a sun hat, and sunscreen as directed for outdoor time. Favour cooler morning or late-afternoon play where practical, and avoid the strongest midday heat.', 5),
(20, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Never leave baby in a parked vehicle, even briefly — temperatures rise dangerously fast, even with windows cracked.', 6),
(21, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Physical confidence keeps growing — running, climbing, and squatting to pick things up may look steadier, though supervision needs stay high as ability outpaces judgment. Secure stairs, windows/balconies, furniture, and TVs, and keep walkways clear and dry.', 0),
(21, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Vocabulary may continue expanding, with two-word phrases more common for some toddlers; wide variation remains completely normal. Respond to what baby says or points to, add a word or two, and pause for their turn rather than testing vocabulary.', 1),
(21, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Baby may begin pointing to a named picture in a book, or to a body part when asked, though this is emerging rather than expected. Make it playful during reading, dressing, and bath time.', 2),
(21, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Growing independence often shows up as "me do it" — wanting to try things alone. This is developmentally healthy even when it is slower or messier; offer a safe choice and time to try.', 3),
(21, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age. Speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills, a concern about communication, or any developmental question.', 4),
(21, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Supporting a toddler''s "me do it" independence takes patience and time that can be in short supply. Letting small tasks take longer is not indulgence — it is genuinely how they learn. Choose one or two moments a day when there is time to practise.', 0),
(21, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Your wellbeing matters too. Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(21, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities. Asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
(21, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; water with and between meals; and continued breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet, but should not crowd out meals. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 0),
(21, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple self-help items can support "me do it" independence: an easy-grip cup, toddler spoon and fork, clothing with large openings, and a sturdy non-slip step stool. Stay beside toddler for water tasks or stool use.', 1),
(21, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue lightweight summer clothing, a sun hat, shade, and sunscreen as directed for outdoor time. Breathable fabrics and a spare set help with sweaty play.', 2),
(21, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and continue avoiding routine screen use, added sugar, juice, and tea. There is no need to pressure toilet training yet; follow readiness and keep practice gentle.', 0),
(21, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pressure around vocabulary, skill timing, or toilet-training readiness. The range stays genuinely wide toward the two-year mark; focus on progress, connection, and discussing questions early with your paediatrician.', 1),
(21, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe active play — running, ball play, supervised climbing, and stairs. Avoid seated wheeled walkers and keep loose mats, cords, and small objects out of busy walking routes.', 0),
(21, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Let baby attempt simple self-help tasks with time and supervision: dressing, hand-washing, tidying a toy, or using a spoon. Offer help only after a real chance to try.', 1),
(21, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(21, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If the 16–24-month vaccination visit is still pending, do not wait — complete it now and take baby''s immunisation card. DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due; JE 2 applies in relevant areas, and Vitamin A may also be due. Private schedules can differ, so confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(21, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep with a firm, age-appropriate cot or bed; avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. Keep brushing teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(21, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(21, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'A more mobile, curious toddler outdoors in summer meets new hazards. Hot surfaces — metal slides, dark car seats, sun-baked pavement, and playground equipment — can burn skin quickly; check the temperature before contact.', 3),
(21, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Continue frequent water, shade, sun protection, and peak-heat avoidance as outdoor exploration increases. Offer water with and between meals and after active play; choose water rather than sweet drinks, and favour cooler morning or late-afternoon play where practical.', 4),
(21, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Mosquito exposure can rise with outdoor play. Use child-safe repellent only as directed; do not apply it to hands, eyes, mouth, cuts, or irritated skin. Use screens or nets where practical, and empty standing water around the home regularly.', 5),
(21, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Never leave baby in a parked vehicle, even briefly — temperatures rise dangerously fast, even with windows cracked.', 6),
(22, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Physical skills keep refining — a toddler may run, kick a ball forward, climb onto low furniture, or walk up a few stairs with help. Coming down stays harder; hold a hand or rail and stay close.', 0),
(22, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Vocabulary may be growing more noticeably, with two-word phrases emerging for some toddlers. Wide variation remains normal right up to two years; respond to words and gestures, add a word or two, and pause for their turn rather than testing.', 1),
(22, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'In familiar routines, baby may begin following a simple two-step request or naming a few familiar pictures or objects. Keep it playful: "Get your cup, then put it here," or point together in a book.', 2),
(22, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Parallel play — playing alongside other children rather than directly with them — is normal and typical now. Do not force sharing; model short turns and keep expectations gentle.', 3),
(22, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age, and speak to your paediatrician about any loss of skills, a specific concern, or a question about communication or development.', 4),
(22, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'As baby reaches two, it is natural to reflect on how far you have both come — mixed feelings about the toddler years arriving are completely normal. You do not have to enjoy every part of this transition to be doing a good job.', 0),
(22, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(22, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities. Asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
(22, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; offer water with and between meals; and continue breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet, but should not crowd out meals. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 0),
(22, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Book or ask whether the two-year well-child visit is due. Take the immunisation card and your questions; ask your paediatrician about growth, sleep, feeding, development, and routine developmental and autism-specific screening.', 1),
(22, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Waterproof, non-slip footwear and quick-dry clothing suit a toddler who wants to explore outdoors through monsoon weather. Keep a dry spare set handy.', 2),
(22, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and continue avoiding routine screen use, added sugar, juice, and tea. There is no need to pressure toilet training yet; follow readiness and keep practice gentle.', 0),
(22, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any pressure around vocabulary, skills, independence, or toilet-training timing. The range stays genuinely wide even at this point; focus on progress, connection, and discussing questions early with your paediatrician.', 1),
(22, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe active play — running, ball play, supervised climbing, and stairs. Secure stairs, windows/balconies, furniture, and TVs; avoid seated wheeled walkers; and keep loose mats, cords, and small objects out of busy walking routes.', 0),
(22, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Playing alongside other children at family gatherings or playgroups supports social development, even without direct interaction yet. Offer brief, supported turns with a toy; sharing will develop gradually.', 1),
(22, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(22, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If the 16–24-month vaccination visit still has not happened, do not delay — complete it now and take baby''s immunisation card. DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due; JE 2 applies in relevant areas, and Vitamin A may also be due. Private schedules can differ, so confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(22, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep with a firm, age-appropriate cot or bed; avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. Keep brushing teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(22, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(22, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'A fast, curious toddler plus monsoon wet surfaces is a real fall combination — keep entryways, bathrooms, and frequently walked paths dry. Secure or remove loose mats, wipe spills promptly, and use non-slip footwear.', 3),
(22, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Avoid floodwater and standing-water play. Use safe drinking water and hygienic food, wash hands and feet after outdoor play, keep cuts covered, and continue mosquito protection as directed. Empty standing water around the home regularly.', 4),
(22, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Seek advice promptly for fever, repeated vomiting, persistent diarrhoea, blood in stool, poor drinking, or unusual sleepiness — especially after contact with floodwater or standing water.', 5),
(22, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Keep clothing, footwear, and bedding fully dry before use to help prevent fungal skin issues in the humidity.', 6),
(23, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'At two, many toddlers run, kick a ball, and walk up a few stairs with help. Coming down stays harder; hold a hand or rail and stay close. Jumping may be emerging — the range stays wide and supervision remains essential.', 0),
(23, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Two-word phrases may be more common now, but variation remains completely normal and gestures are valid communication. Respond to what baby says or points to, add a word or two, and pause for their turn rather than testing vocabulary.', 1),
(23, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple pretend play, pointing to named pictures or body parts, and following familiar two-step routines may be emerging. Keep it playful during reading, dressing, bath time, and everyday tasks.', 2),
(23, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Parallel play continues — playing alongside rather than with other children is normal. Do not force sharing; model short turns and keep expectations gentle.', 3),
(23, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'As always, use corrected age for babies born prematurely rather than calendar age, and raise any loss of skills, a specific concern, or a question about communication or development with your paediatrician at the two-year visit.', 4),
(23, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Two full years — this is a real milestone for you, not just for your child. However this journey has actually gone, you have carried it, and that deserves acknowledging. You do not have to enjoy every part of parenting to be doing a good job.', 0),
(23, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(23, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities — that does not expire at two years. Asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
(23, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; offer water with and between meals; and continue breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet, but should not crowd out meals. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 0),
(23, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Book the two-year well-child visit if it is not already scheduled. Take the immunisation card and your questions; ask about growth, feeding, sleep, development, and routine developmental and autism-specific screening.', 1),
(23, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Age-appropriate toys that grow with this stage — simple puzzles, building blocks, picture books, pretend-play items, and a toddler spoon/fork for everyday practice.', 2),
(23, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and continue avoiding routine screen use, added sugar, juice, and tea. There is no need to pressure toilet training; follow readiness and keep practice gentle.', 0),
(23, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Any pressure around hitting specific milestones exactly at two, vocabulary, independence, sharing, or toilet-training timing. The range stays genuinely wide at this checkpoint; focus on progress, connection, and discussing questions early with your paediatrician.', 1),
(23, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe active play — running, ball play, supervised climbing, and jumping practice. Secure stairs, windows/balconies, furniture, and TVs; avoid seated wheeled walkers; and keep loose mats, cords, and small objects out of busy walking routes.', 0),
(23, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pretend play, simple puzzles, shared reading, and brief supported turns with a toy suit this stage well. Let baby try simple self-help tasks with time and close supervision.', 1),
(23, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(23, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Attend the two-year well-child visit. Ask about growth, feeding, sleep, development, and routine developmental and autism-specific screening. If the 16–24-month vaccination visit is still pending, complete it now and take baby''s immunisation card: DPT booster 1, MR 2, and OPV booster are commonly due; JE 2 applies in relevant areas, and Vitamin A may also be due. Private schedules can differ, so confirm with your paediatrician.', 0),
(23, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep with a firm, age-appropriate cot or bed; avoid heavy loose bedding, pillows, and overheating. A cot-to-toddler-bed transition may become relevant now or later depending on climbing and size — there is no fixed timeline. Keep brushing teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(23, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(23, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Keep monsoon fall precautions practical: dry entryways, bathrooms, and frequently walked paths; secure or remove loose mats; wipe spills promptly; and use non-slip footwear. Avoid floodwater and standing-water play.', 3),
(23, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Use safe drinking water and hygienic food, wash hands and feet after outdoor play, keep cuts covered, and continue mosquito protection as directed. Empty standing water around the home regularly, and keep footwear, clothing, and bedding fully dry before use.', 4),
(23, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Seek advice promptly for fever, repeated vomiting, persistent diarrhoea, blood in stool, poor drinking, or unusual sleepiness — especially after contact with standing or floodwater.', 5),
(24, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Physical skills keep refining — a toddler may walk up and down stairs with both feet on each step, kick a ball, and run more smoothly, though supervision stays essential.', 0),
(24, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Vocabulary often grows in this stretch; two-word phrases become more common, and some toddlers begin short three-word combinations, though wide variation remains normal.', 1),
(24, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple sorting, matching, and following two-step instructions may be emerging through everyday play.', 2),
(24, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pretend play may grow richer — a doll "eats," then "sleeps" — reflecting memory and imagination building together.', 3),
(24, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'For children born significantly premature, discuss development using your paediatrician''s guidance rather than calendar age alone, and raise any loss of skills or specific concern.', 4),
(24, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'The stretch past two often brings new negotiation — a toddler with more words and more opinions. Simple, consistent limits tend to work better than lengthy explanations in the moment: name the feeling, hold a short calm limit, offer two safe choices, reconnect once calm returns.', 0),
(24, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue watching for the same wellbeing signs named across recent months; support remains just as valid now, and urgent help is warranted for any thoughts of harm to yourself or others.', 1),
(24, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities.', 2),
(24, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Offer 3–4 varied family meals and 1–2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; water with and between meals; and continued breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet but should not crowd out meals. Encourage, do not force, eating.', 0),
(24, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple puzzles and sorting toys that grow with developing skills suit this stage. Choose sturdy pieces without small detachable parts, magnets, or button batteries.', 1),
(24, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Warm, movement-friendly winter clothing as an active toddler spends more time indoors during cold weather.', 2),
(24, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard raw pieces, hard sweets, button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects remain unsafe or out of reach. Modify food shape and texture, supervise eating within arm''s reach, and keep routine screen use adult-supported and limited; continue avoiding added sugar, juice, and tea.', 0),
(24, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'No pressure on toilet training — follow readiness gently. Any pressure around vocabulary size or skill timing — the range stays genuinely wide through the third year.', 1),
(24, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe active play — running, ball play, climbing, and stair practice with supervision. Secure furniture, TVs, windows/balconies, and stairs; a climbing toddler reaches higher than expected.', 0),
(24, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pretend play, simple puzzles, and shared reading suit this stage well.', 1),
(24, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'For you: continue whatever movement and rest rhythm feels sustainable.', 2),
(24, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'No routine UIP vaccine dose is due this month if the card is up to date; Vitamin A continues every six months from 16–18 months to age five (confirm the card and local/private schedule). Your paediatrician may see baby for growth or concerns in between.', 0),
(24, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe sleep; a cot-to-toddler-bed transition may be relevant around now or later, depending on climbing and size. Keep brushing teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste.', 1),
(24, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual sleepiness, poor drinking or dehydration, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. For fever or illness that worries you, contact your paediatrician promptly.', 2),
(24, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Keep burn risks in check with an active, curious toddler: active barriers around heaters and cooking areas, hot drinks and hot water out of reach, and a bathwater check before use.', 3),
(24, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Dry winter air affects skin — moisturise regularly, especially after bathing. If using a humidifier, clean and dry it daily as directed and avoid overheating the room.', 4),
(24, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'winter', null, 'Cold-and-flu season means continued handwashing before meals and after outside play, and reasonable caution with unwell visitors as a toddler socialises more.', 5),
(25, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Physical play grows bolder — jumping with both feet, walking on tiptoe, or climbing may be emerging, though coordination and supervision needs stay high.', 0),
(25, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Language often expands — some toddlers use short phrases and are understood by family much of the time, though clarity to others is still developing and wide variation remains normal.', 1),
(25, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Beginning to understand simple concepts — "big/small," "in/out," one vs. many — may emerge through everyday play.', 2),
(25, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pretend play may include more sequence and role — "cooking" then "feeding" a doll — reflecting growing memory and social understanding.', 3),
(25, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'For children born significantly premature, discuss development using your paediatrician''s guidance rather than calendar age alone, and raise any loss of skills or specific concern.', 4),
