(33, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple sorting, counting games, picture talk, and cooperative pretend scenes support thinking and language naturally. Let toddler try small self-help tasks with time and close supervision rather than turning play into a test.', 1),
(33, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use a correctly fitted child car restraint suitable for your toddler''s height and weight on every car journey. Keep it rear-facing while your child remains within the seat maker''s rear-facing limits.', 2),
(33, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If your child is up to date, no routine UIP vaccine dose is scheduled this month. Vitamin A continues every six months from 16-18 months until age five; confirm the card and next due date with your paediatrician or local programme, as private schedules and local services may differ. Plan a three-year paediatric visit to discuss growth, development, dental care, and any concerns.', 0),
(33, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If your toddler tries to climb out of the cot, plan a safe sleep arrangement rather than waiting for a fall: follow the cot maker''s guidance, consider a low age-appropriate bed when needed, toddler-proof the room, and gate stairs if needed. Brush teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(33, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual difficulty waking, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. Contact your paediatrician promptly for poor drinking or dehydration, repeated vomiting or diarrhoea, blood in stool, fever that worries you, or a child who seems much less alert than usual.', 2),
(33, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'As a toddler eats and drinks more independently in summer, food and water safety in heat matters: offer freshly prepared food, refrigerate promptly, reheat thoroughly, use safe drinking water, and discard food left out in warm weather.', 3),
(33, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Continue the core summer set: frequent water, shade, a sun hat, sunscreen used as directed, hot-surface checks, within-arm''s-reach water supervision, and outdoor play in the coolest practical hours.', 4),
(33, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Mosquito risk may be high locally. Use age-appropriate mosquito protection only as directed, reduce standing water, and use nets or screens where practical.', 5),
(33, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'summer', null, 'Never leave a toddler in a parked vehicle, even briefly - temperatures rise dangerously fast, even with windows cracked.', 6),
(34, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Physical skills keep refining - a toddler may run confidently, jump with both feet, climb stairs with more ease, or enjoy simple balance and obstacle play. Wide variation remains normal, and close supervision is still needed.', 0),
(34, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Language often continues expanding - some toddlers hold short back-and-forth conversations, ask who/what/where questions, name actions in a picture or book, and are understood by others more of the time. Clarity, sentence length, and language mix still vary widely, especially in multilingual homes.', 1),
(34, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Everyday thinking grows through play: sorting and matching, enjoying number words and counting games, following a familiar routine, or starting to understand words such as now, next, and later may emerge. Keep it playful, not a skill to test.', 2),
(34, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pretend play may become even more elaborate - extended scenes, simple role reversal, and cooperative play with peers, reflecting maturing imagination and social skill.', 3),
(34, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'For children born significantly premature, ask your paediatrician how to interpret development for them. Raise any loss of skills, a specific concern, or a question about communication or development promptly.', 4),
(34, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'With the third birthday approaching, it is natural to reflect on this stretch of the journey - mixed feelings are normal, and there is no need to feel a certain way about it.', 0),
(34, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond toddler-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(34, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count; asking for help is part of caring for your family, not a failure to manage.', 2),
