(34, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Everyday materials support learning without special purchases: books, crayons, blocks, large-piece puzzles, and safe pretend props such as plastic cups, spoons, or scarves. Talk about colours, actions, and numbers during daily routines; avoid small detachable parts, sharp edges, batteries, and unsafe cupboards or rooms.', 1),
(34, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Waterproof, non-slip footwear and quick-dry clothing are worth arranging for monsoon outdoor exploration.', 2),
(34, 'hold_off', 'any', 'any', null, 'Keep food and household-safety boundaries: avoid whole nuts, whole grapes, popcorn, hard sweets, and hard raw pieces; keep eating seated and supervised; and lock button batteries, magnets, medicines, cleaners, and small objects away. If screens are used, keep them to no more than one hour a day of children''s content with an adult present, away from meals, bedtime, and the bedroom. Follow toilet-training readiness gently, with no pressure around speech clarity, counting, or skill timing.', 0),
(34, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue safe active play - running, climbing, ball play, and supervised stairs. Secure furniture, TVs, windows/balconies, and stairs; keep loose mats, cords, and small objects out of busy walking routes; and avoid seated wheeled walkers.', 0),
(34, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Simple sorting, counting games, picture talk, and cooperative pretend scenes support thinking and language naturally. Let toddler try small self-help tasks with time and close supervision rather than turning play into a test.', 1),
(34, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use a correctly fitted child car restraint suitable for your toddler''s height and weight on every journey. Keep it rear-facing while your child remains within the seat maker''s rear-facing limits.', 2),
(34, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If your child is up to date, no routine UIP vaccine dose is scheduled this month. Vitamin A continues every six months from 16-18 months until age five; confirm the card and next due date with your paediatrician or local programme, as private schedules and local services may differ. Plan the upcoming three-year paediatric visit to discuss growth, development, dental care, and any concerns.', 0),
(34, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If your toddler tries to climb out of the cot, plan a safe sleep arrangement rather than waiting for a fall: follow the cot maker''s guidance, consider a low age-appropriate bed when needed, toddler-proof the room, and gate stairs if needed. Brush teeth twice daily with a rice-grain smear of fluoride toothpaste and arrange a dental visit if one has not yet happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
(34, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek urgent care for breathing difficulty, a seizure, unusual difficulty waking, a serious injury, suspected poisoning, or choking. Contact your paediatrician promptly for poor drinking or dehydration, repeated vomiting or diarrhoea, blood in stool, fever that worries you, or a child who seems much less alert than usual.', 2),
(34, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'A fast, independent toddler plus monsoon wet surfaces is a real fall risk: keep entryways, bathrooms, and walked paths dry; use non-slip footwear; and avoid floodwater, open drains, and standing water.', 3),
(34, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'After heavy rain or flooding, waterborne and mosquito risks may increase locally. Use safe drinking water, wash hands with soap after contact with floodwater and before food, keep food hygienic, and use age-appropriate mosquito protection only as directed. Do not use floodwater to wash food or dishes, and discard food that has touched floodwater.', 4),
(34, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Contact your paediatrician promptly for fever, persistent vomiting or diarrhoea, blood in stool, reduced urination or poor drinking, or unusual lethargy - especially after contact with standing or floodwater.', 5),
(34, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'monsoon', null, 'Change damp clothing promptly and keep footwear, clothing, bedding, and skin folds dry. Ask for medical advice if an itchy or red skin rash is spreading, oozing, or causing pain.', 6),
(35, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'At three, a child may run well, climb with growing confidence, pedal a tricycle, or enjoy simple jumping games. The range stays wide, and close supervision remains important.', 0),
(35, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Language often becomes more useful in daily life - some children speak in sentences, have short back-and-forth conversations, ask many questions, and are understood by others most of the time. Multilingual homes and individual variation remain completely normal.', 1),
(35, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Everyday thinking and self-help grow through play: a child may copy a circle when shown, use a fork, help put on simple clothing, follow familiar two- or three-step requests, and enjoy sorting and counting games. Keep it playful, not a skill to test.', 2),
(35, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'Pretend play may be rich and social - extended stories, cooperative play with other children, and simple role-taking, reflecting growing imagination and connection.', 3),
(35, 'baby_development', 'any', 'any', null, 'For children born significantly premature, ask your paediatrician how to interpret development for them. Raise any loss of skills or specific concern at the three-year visit.', 4),
(35, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Three years — this is a genuine milestone for you too, not just your child. However this journey actually went, the hard stretches and the good ones both, you carried it, and that''s real.', 0),
(35, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Seek support from your doctor or a trusted person if low mood, anxiety, anger, hopelessness, sleep trouble beyond child-related waking, or feeling unable to cope is lasting or worsening. Urgent help is needed if you feel unsafe or have thoughts of harming yourself or someone else.', 1),
(35, 'mum_wellbeing', 'any', 'any', null, 'Rest, shared care, and small moments for yourself remain valid priorities - that does not end at three years, or ever. A short walk, stretch, or quiet break can count.', 2),
(35, 'buy_now', 'any', 'any', null, 'Continue 3-4 varied family meals and 1-2 nutritious snacks according to appetite. Include iron-rich foods such as dals/beans, eggs, meat/fish where eaten, and leafy vegetables; offer water with and between meals; and continue breastfeeding if you both wish. Cow''s milk or dairy can be part of the diet, but should not crowd out meals. Cut grapes lengthways into quarters and serve nuts crushed/ground or as smooth paste. Encourage, but do not force, eating.', 0),
