(35, 'movement_rest', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use a correctly fitted child car restraint suitable for your child''s height and weight on every journey. Keep it rear-facing while your child remains within the seat maker''s rear-facing limits.', 2),
(35, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'Use the three-year paediatric visit to discuss growth, development, dental care, and any concerns. If the card is up to date, no routine UIP vaccine dose is due this month; Vitamin A continues every six months from 16-18 months until age five. Confirm the card and next due date with your paediatrician or local programme, as private schedules and local services may differ.', 0),
(35, 'appointments_safety', 'any', 'any', null, 'If your child climbs out of the cot, plan a safe sleep arrangement rather than waiting for a fall: follow the cot maker''s guidance, consider a low age-appropriate bed when needed, toddler-proof the room, and gate stairs if needed. Brush teeth twice daily with a pea-sized amount of fluoride toothpaste; help with brushing and arrange a dental visit if one has not happened or if you have concerns.', 1),
